    "#### geglättet XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateipfade\n",
    "path_reanalysis = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_12_total_precipitation_reanalysis_historical.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_45 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_12_total_precipitation_projections_rcp_4_5.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_85 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_12_total_precipitation_projections_rcp_8_5.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Einlesen der Daten\n",
    "df_reanalysis = pd.read_csv(path_reanalysis)\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_45)\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_85)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertieren der Zeitspalte in Datetime-Objekte\n",
    "df_reanalysis['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_reanalysis['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_45['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_45['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_85['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_85['time'])\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_fixed_30_year_average(df, column):\n",
    "    df['30_year_avg'] = None\n",
    "    df['30_year_std'] = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Füge eine Spalte für das Jahr hinzu, falls noch nicht vorhanden\n",
    "    df['Year'] = df['time'].dt.year\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "        current_year = row['Year']\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Bestimme den Zeitraum von 15 Jahren vor und 15 Jahren nach dem aktuellen Jahr\n",
    "        start_year = current_year - 15\n",
    "        end_year = current_year + 14\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Filtere die Daten, die in diesen Zeitraum fallen\n",
    "        period_data = df[(df['Year'] >= start_year) & (df['Year'] <= end_year)]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Berechne den Durchschnitt und die Standardabweichung für den Zeitraum\n",
    "        if len(period_data) == 30:  # Nur wenn genau 30 Jahre im Zeitraum sind\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_avg'] = period_data[column].mean()\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_std'] = period_data[column].std()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = compute_fixed_30_year_average(df_rcp_45, 'prAdjust')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = compute_fixed_30_year_average(df_rcp_85, 'prAdjust')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Daten basierend auf den Jahren\n",
    "df_reanalysis = df_reanalysis[(df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year >= 1940) & (df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year <= 2023)]\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = df_rcp_45[(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = df_rcp_85[(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reanalyse-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_reanalysis['time'], df_reanalysis['tp'], **design_reanalyse)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'], **design_rcp45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardabweichung für RCP4.5 als obere und untere Grenze plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.1)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Gefüllte Fläche für die Standardabweichung von RCP4.5\n",
    "# plt.fill_between(df_rcp_45['time'], \n",
    "#                  df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "#                  df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "#                  color='blue', alpha=0.05, label='RCP4.5 - Std')\n",

    "## Anomalie Reanalyse-Daten\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Lese die CSV-Datei ein\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_12_total_precipitation_reanalysis_historical.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertiere die 'time'-Spalte in Datetime-Format\n",
    "df['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df['time'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Berechnung des Mittelwerts für den Referenzzeitraum 1981-2010\n",
    "reference_period = df[(df['time'].dt.year >= 1981) & (df['time'].dt.year <= 2010)]\n",
    "reference_mean = reference_period['tp'].mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Berechnung der Anomalien\n",
    "df['anomaly'] = df['tp'] - reference_mean\n",
    "\n",
    "# Anzeigen der berechneten Anomalien\n",
    "print(df[['time', 'tp', 'anomaly']].head(20))  # Erste 20 Zeilen anzeigen\n",
    "print(df[['time', 'tp', 'anomaly']].tail(20))  # Letzte 20 Zeilen anzeigen\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot der negativen Werte\n",
    "plt.bar(df['time'][df['anomaly'] < 0], \n",
    "        df['anomaly'][df['anomaly'] < 0], \n",
    "        width=200, color='#005d82', label='Negative Abweichung')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot der positiven Werte\n",
    "plt.bar(df['time'][df['anomaly'] >= 0], \n",
    "        df['anomaly'][df['anomaly'] >= 0], \n",
    "        width=200, color='#ce1657', label='Positive Abweichung')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.axhline(0, color='black', linewidth=0.8)\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Jahr', **design_xlabel)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Anomalie des Gesamtniederschlages', **design_ylabel)\n",
    "plt.title('Referenzzeitraum 1981-2010', fontsize=12, x=0.5, ha='center')\n",
    "plt.suptitle(f'Anomalie des Gesamtniederschlages in {aoi_name}', **design_title)\n",
    "plt.grid(**design_grid)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X-Achse: Zeige alle 5 Jahre\n",
    "years = pd.date_range(start=df['time'].min(), end=df['time'].max(), freq='5YE').year\n",
    "plt.xticks(pd.to_datetime(years, format='%Y'), years, rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend(loc='lower center', bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.24), ncol=2)  # Legende unterhalb der Grafik platzieren\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Untertitel\n",
    "plt.figtext(0.5, -0.05, untertitel , **design_figtext)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Zeige das Plot\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]

    "#### Plot: HeatwaveDays (Datensatz HWD liefert genauere Daten)\n",
    "Der Index Klimatologische Hitzewellentage zählt die Anzahl der Tage in einem Jahr innerhalb längerer Perioden mit ungewöhnlich hohen Temperaturen. Eine Hitzewelle ist nach der klimatologischen EURO-CORDEX-Definition ein Zeitraum von mindestens drei aufeinanderfolgenden Tagen, an denen die Tageshöchsttemperatur das 99. Perzentil der Tageshöchsttemperaturen der Saison Mai bis September während des Kontrollzeitraums Zeitraum 1971-2000."
   ]

    "### LINEAR GEGLÄTTET\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateipfade\n",
    "path_reanalysis = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_09_heat_waves_climatological_reanalysis_historical.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_45 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_09_heat_waves_climatological_projections_rcp_4_5.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_85 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_09_heat_waves_climatological_projections_rcp_8_5.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Einlesen der Daten\n",
    "df_reanalysis = pd.read_csv(path_reanalysis)\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_45)\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_85)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertieren der Zeitspalte in Datetime-Objekte\n",
    "df_reanalysis['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_reanalysis['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_45['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_45['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_85['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_85['time'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Daten basierend auf den Jahren\n",
    "df_reanalysis = df_reanalysis[(df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year >= 1940) & (df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year <= 2023)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Berechnen des 30-jährigen gleitenden Durchschnitts\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_fixed_30_year_average(df, column):\n",
    "    df['30_year_avg'] = None\n",
    "    df['30_year_std'] = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Füge eine Spalte für das Jahr hinzu, falls noch nicht vorhanden\n",
    "    df['Year'] = df['time'].dt.year\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "        current_year = row['Year']\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Bestimme den Zeitraum von 15 Jahren vor und 15 Jahren nach dem aktuellen Jahr\n",
    "        start_year = current_year - 15\n",
    "        end_year = current_year + 14\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Filtere die Daten, die in diesen Zeitraum fallen\n",
    "        period_data = df[(df['Year'] >= start_year) & (df['Year'] <= end_year)]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Berechne den Durchschnitt und die Standardabweichung für den Zeitraum\n",
    "        if len(period_data) == 30:  # Nur wenn genau 30 Jahre im Zeitraum sind\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_avg'] = period_data[column].mean()\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_std'] = period_data[column].std()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = compute_fixed_30_year_average(df_rcp_45, 'data')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = compute_fixed_30_year_average(df_rcp_85, 'data')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reanalyse-Daten plotten\n",
    "#plt.plot(df_reanalysis['time'], df_reanalysis['data'], **design_reanalyse)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Projektionen auf den Zeitraum 2024 -> 2085\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = df_rcp_45[(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year >= 1986) & (df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year <= 2085)]\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = df_rcp_85[(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year >= 1986) & (df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year <= 2085)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Umwandeln Dateityp Object in Float\n",
    "df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "df_rcp_85['30_year_std'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "df_rcp_45['30_year_std'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'], **design_rcp45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardabweichung für RCP4.5 als obere und untere Grenze plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# # # Gefüllte Fläche für die Standardabweichung von RCP4.5\n",
    "plt.fill_between(df_rcp_45['time'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 color='blue', alpha=0.05, label='RCP4.5 - Std')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'], **design_rcp85)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='red', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='red', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Gefüllte Fläche für die Standardabweichung von RCP8.5\n",
    "plt.fill_between(df_rcp_85['time'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 color='red', alpha=0.05, label='RCP8.5 - Std')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vertikale Linie zwischen 2023 und 2024 hinzufügen\n",
    "#plt.axvline(x=pd.Timestamp('2024-01-01'), **design_trennlinie)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot-Parameter\n",
    "# plt.xlim(pd.Timestamp('1986-01-01'), pd.Timestamp('2085-01-01'))\n",
    "plt.xlim(pd.Timestamp('2025-01-01'), pd.Timestamp('2085-01-01'))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'].max() + 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Jahr', **design_xlabel)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Hitzewellen-Tage [d]', **design_ylabel)\n",
    "# plt.title(f'Anzahl der Hitzewellen-Tage in {aoi_name}', **design_title)\n",
    "plt.title(f'Projektion der Hitzewellen-Tage in {aoi_name}', **design_title)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(**design_grid)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Untertitel\n",
    "plt.figtext(0.5, -0.05, untertitel, **design_figtext)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X-Achse: 10 Jahre-Intervall\n",
    "#years = pd.date_range(start='1986-01-01', end='2085-01-01', freq='10YE').year\n",
    "years = pd.date_range(start='1985-01-01', end='2085-01-01', freq='10YE').year\n",
    "plt.xticks(pd.to_datetime(years, format='%Y'), years, rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot speichern und anzeigen\n",
    "plt.savefig(f'09_heat_waves_climatological_gegl_proj_{aoi_name}.png')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"

   "source": [
    "#### 13.Maximaler aufeinanderfolgender Fünf-Tage-Niederschlag\n",
    "\n",
    "Maximaler aufeinanderfolgender Fünf-Tage-Niederschlag\" (d. h. die größte Niederschlagssumme an fünf aufeinanderfolgenden Tagen in einem Jahr) ist ein Index von hoher Priorität. Er berücksichtigt das Ausmaß des Ereignisses, ist leicht zu interpretieren und wird häufig in hydrologischen Anwendungen verwendet.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Indikator: Maximaler aufeinanderfolgender Fünf-Tage-Niederschlag\n",
    "- Einheit: mm/5-Tage\n",
    "- Beschreibung: Maximale Fünf-Tages-Niederschlagssummen über ein Jahr."
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateipfade\n",
    "path_reanalysis = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_13_maximum_five_days_precipitation_reanalysis_historical.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_45 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_13_maximum_five_days_precipitation_projections_rcp_4_5.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_85 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_13_maximum_five_days_precipitation_projections_rcp_8_5.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Einlesen der Daten\n",
    "df_reanalysis = pd.read_csv(path_reanalysis)\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_45)\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_85)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertieren der Zeitspalte in Datetime-Objekte\n",
    "df_reanalysis['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_reanalysis['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_45['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_45['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_85['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_85['time'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Daten basierend auf den Jahren\n",
    "df_reanalysis = df_reanalysis[(df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year >= 1940) & (df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year <= 2023)]\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = df_rcp_45[(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = df_rcp_85[(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reanalyse-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_reanalysis['time'], df_reanalysis['tp'], **design_reanalyse)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['prAdjust'], **design_rcp45)\n",
    "# # Trendlinie für RCP4.5 berechnen und plotten\n",
    "z = np.polyfit(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year, df_rcp_45['prAdjust'], 1)\n",
    "p = np.poly1d(z)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], p(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year), **design_rcp45_trend)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['prAdjust'], **design_rcp85)\n",
    "# # Trendlinie für RCP8.5 berechnen und plotten\n",
    "z = np.polyfit(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year, df_rcp_85['prAdjust'], 1)\n",
    "p = np.poly1d(z)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], p(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year), **design_rcp85_trend)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vertikale Linie zwischen 2023 und 2024 hinzufügen\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=pd.Timestamp('2024-01-01'), **design_trennlinie)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlim(df_reanalysis['time'].min(), df_rcp_45['time'].max())\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, df_rcp_85['prAdjust'].max() + 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Jahr', **design_xlabel)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Niederschlag [mm/5-Tage]', **design_ylabel)\n",
    "plt.title(f'Maximale aufeinanderfolgende 5-Tages Niederschlag in {aoi_name}', **design_grid)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Untertitel\n",
    "plt.figtext(0.5, -0.05, untertitel , **design_figtext)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X-Achse: 10 Jahre-Intervall\n",
    "years = pd.date_range(start=df_reanalysis['time'].min(), end=df_rcp_85['time'].max(), freq='10YE').year\n",
    "plt.xticks(pd.to_datetime(years, format='%Y'), years, rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n"

   },
   "source": [
    "#### 14. Extremnniederschläge insgesamt\n",
    "\n",
    "Die \"Summe der extremen Niederschläge\" (d. h. die Summe der Niederschlagswerte an allen Tagen, die über einem festgelegten Schwellenwert liegen, der über einen Bezugszeitraum definiert wurde) ist ein Index von hoher Priorität. Er berücksichtigt die Häufigkeit und das Ausmaß ungewöhnlicher Niederschlagsereignisse, die im Vergleich zu den Ausgangsbedingungen festgestellt wurden. \n",
    "\n",
    "- Indikator: Extremniederschläge insgesamt\n",
    "- Einheit: mm\n",
    "- Beschreibung: Die Gesamtsumme der Tagesniederschlagswerte in einem Jahr, die das 99. Perzentil des Bezugszeitraums überschreiten."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

    "# Einlesen der Daten\n",

    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], p(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year), **design_rcp85_trend)\n",
    "\n",

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 37,
   "id": "cde4c29f-8d2c-44bf-afad-f22e54d2a98d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "### LINEAR GEGLÄTTET\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateipfade\n",
    "path_reanalysis = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_14_extreme_precipitation_total_reanalysis_historical.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_45 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_14_extreme_precipitation_total_projections_rcp_4_5.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_85 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_14_extreme_precipitation_total_projections_rcp_8_5.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Einlesen der Daten\n",
    "df_reanalysis = pd.read_csv(path_reanalysis)\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_45)\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_85)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertieren der Zeitspalte in Datetime-Objekte\n",
    "df_reanalysis['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_reanalysis['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_45['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_45['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_85['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_85['time'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Daten basierend auf den Jahren\n",
    "df_reanalysis = df_reanalysis[(df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year >= 1940) & (df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year <= 2023)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Berechnen des 30-jährigen gleitenden Durchschnitts\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_fixed_30_year_average(df, column):\n",
    "    df['30_year_avg'] = None\n",
    "    df['30_year_std'] = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Füge eine Spalte für das Jahr hinzu, falls noch nicht vorhanden\n",
    "    df['Year'] = df['time'].dt.year\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "        current_year = row['Year']\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Bestimme den Zeitraum von 15 Jahren vor und 15 Jahren nach dem aktuellen Jahr\n",
    "        start_year = current_year - 15\n",
    "        end_year = current_year + 14\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Filtere die Daten, die in diesen Zeitraum fallen\n",
    "        period_data = df[(df['Year'] >= start_year) & (df['Year'] <= end_year)]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Berechne den Durchschnitt und die Standardabweichung für den Zeitraum\n",
    "        if len(period_data) == 30:  # Nur wenn genau 30 Jahre im Zeitraum sind\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_avg'] = period_data[column].mean()\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_std'] = period_data[column].std()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = compute_fixed_30_year_average(df_rcp_45, 'data')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = compute_fixed_30_year_average(df_rcp_85, 'data')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reanalyse-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_reanalysis['time'], df_reanalysis['data'], **design_reanalyse)\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Fülle NaN-Werte in den Spalten '30_year_avg' und '30_year_std' auf (optional: z.B. mit 0)\n",
    "# df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'].fillna(0, inplace=True)\n",
    "# df_rcp_45['30_year_std'].fillna(0, inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'].fillna(0, inplace=True)\n",
    "# df_rcp_85['30_year_std'].fillna(0, inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = df_rcp_45[(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year <= 2084)]\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = df_rcp_85[(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year <= 2084)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'], **design_rcp45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardabweichung für RCP4.5 als obere und untere Grenze plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "df_rcp_85['30_year_std'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "df_rcp_45['30_year_std'] = pd.to_numeric(df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], errors='coerce')\n",
    "\n",
    "# # # Gefüllte Fläche für die Standardabweichung von RCP4.5\n",
    "plt.fill_between(df_rcp_45['time'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 color='blue', alpha=0.05, label='RCP4.5 - Std')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'], **design_rcp85)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='red', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='red', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# # Gefüllte Fläche für die Standardabweichung von RCP8.5\n",
    "plt.fill_between(df_rcp_85['time'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 color='red', alpha=0.05, label='RCP8.5 - Std')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vertikale Linie zwischen 2023 und 2024 hinzufügen\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=pd.Timestamp('2024-01-01'), **design_trennlinie)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot-Parameter\n",
    "#plt.xlim(df_reanalysis['time'].min(), df_rcp_45['time'].max())\n",
    "plt.xlim(pd.Timestamp('1965-01-01'), pd.Timestamp('2085-01-01'))\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'].max() + 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Jahr', **design_xlabel)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Extremniederschläge insgesamt [mm]', **design_ylabel)\n",
    "plt.title(f'Extremniederschläge insgesamt für {aoi_name}', **design_title)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(**design_grid)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Untertitel\n",
    "plt.figtext(0.5, -0.05, untertitel, **design_figtext)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X-Achse: 10 Jahre-Intervall\n",
    "years = pd.date_range(start='1965-01-01', end='2085-01-01', freq='10YE').year\n",
    "plt.xticks(pd.to_datetime(years, format='%Y'), years, rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot speichern und anzeigen\n",
    "plt.savefig(f'14_extreme_precipitation_total_gegl_{aoi_name}.png')\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0e13e86a-447a-4965-a4f3-b1e27e476f56",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### 15 Aufeinanderfolgende Trockentage\n",
    "\n",
    "\"Aufeinanderfolgende Trockentage\" (d. h. der längste Zeitraum aufeinander folgender Tage mit weniger als 1 mm Niederschlag) ist ein Index mittlerer Priorität, der die Dauer der Trockenheit berücksichtigt. Er lässt sich leicht berechnen, bietet aber nur einen begrenzten Mehrwert gegenüber den anderen Trockenheits- und Dürreindizes.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Indikator: Aufeinanderfolgende trockene Tage\n",
    "- Einheit: Tag [d]\n",
    "- Beschreibung: Der längste Zeitraum aufeinander folgender Tage mit Tagesniederschlägen unter 1 mm in einem Jahr, einer Jahreszeit oder einem Monat."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "id": "81effd70-8596-43cd-922f-71d39e0934e7",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateipfade\n",
    "path_reanalysis = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_18_consecutive_dry_days_reanalysis_historical.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_45 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_18_consecutive_dry_days_projections_rcp_4_5.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_85 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_18_consecutive_dry_days_projections_rcp_8_5.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Einlesen der Daten\n",
    "df_reanalysis = pd.read_csv(path_reanalysis)\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_45)\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_85)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertieren der Zeitspalte in Datetime-Objekte\n",
    "df_reanalysis['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_reanalysis['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_45['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_45['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_85['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_85['time'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Daten basierend auf den Jahren\n",
    "df_reanalysis = df_reanalysis[(df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year >= 1940) & (df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year <= 2023)]\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = df_rcp_45[(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = df_rcp_85[(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reanalyse-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_reanalysis['time'], df_reanalysis['cdd'], **design_reanalyse)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['cdd'], **design_rcp45)\n",
    "# # Trendlinie für RCP4.5 berechnen und plotten\n",
    "z = np.polyfit(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year, df_rcp_45['cdd'], 1)\n",
    "p = np.poly1d(z)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], p(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year), **design_rcp45_trend)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['cdd'], **design_rcp85)\n",
    "# # Trendlinie für RCP8.5 berechnen und plotten\n",
    "z = np.polyfit(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year, df_rcp_85['cdd'], 1)\n",
    "p = np.poly1d(z)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], p(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year), **design_rcp85_trend)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vertikale Linie zwischen 2023 und 2024 hinzufügen\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=pd.Timestamp('2024-01-01'), **design_trennlinie)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlim(df_reanalysis['time'].min(), df_rcp_45['time'].max())\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, df_reanalysis['cdd'].max() + 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Jahr', **design_xlabel)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Trockentage [d]', **design_ylabel)\n",
    "plt.title(f'Aufeinanderfolgende Trockentage für {aoi_name}', **design_title)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(**design_grid)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Untertitel\n",
    "plt.figtext(0.5, -0.05, untertitel , **design_figtext)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X-Achse: 10 Jahre-Intervall\n",
    "years = pd.date_range(start=df_reanalysis['time'].min(), end=df_rcp_85['time'].max(), freq='10YE').year\n",
    "plt.xticks(pd.to_datetime(years, format='%Y'), years, rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",

   "execution_count": 42,
   "id": "efa50d36-2e88-4153-9069-afa22d79d589",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateipfade\n",
    "path_reanalysis = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_18_consecutive_dry_days_reanalysis_historical.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_45 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_18_consecutive_dry_days_projections_rcp_4_5.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_85 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_18_consecutive_dry_days_projections_rcp_8_5.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_fixed_30_year_average(df, column):\n",
    "    df['30_year_avg'] = None\n",
    "    df['30_year_std'] = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "        current_year = row['Year']\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Bestimme den Zeitraum von 15 Jahren vor und 15 Jahren nach dem aktuellen Jahr\n",
    "        start_year = current_year - 15\n",
    "        end_year = current_year + 14\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Filtere die Daten, die in diesen Zeitraum fallen\n",
    "        period_data = df[(df['Year'] >= start_year) & (df['Year'] <= end_year)]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Berechne den Durchschnitt und die Standardabweichung für den Zeitraum\n",
    "        if len(period_data) == 30:  # Nur wenn genau 30 Jahre im Zeitraum sind\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_avg'] = period_data[column].mean()\n",
    "            df.at[i, '30_year_std'] = period_data[column].std()\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return df\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = compute_30_year_average(df_rcp_45, 'cdd')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten glätten\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = compute_30_year_average(df_rcp_85, 'cdd')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Daten basierend auf den Jahren\n",
    "df_reanalysis = df_reanalysis[(df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year >= 1940) & (df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year <= 2023)]\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = df_rcp_45[(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = df_rcp_85[(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reanalyse-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_reanalysis['time'], df_reanalysis['cdd'], **design_reanalyse)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'], **design_rcp45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardabweichung für RCP4.5 als obere und untere Grenze plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.1)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='blue', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gefüllte Fläche für die Standardabweichung von RCP4.5\n",
    "plt.fill_between(df_rcp_45['time'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_45['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_45['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 color='blue', alpha=0.05, label='RCP4.5 - Std')\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'], **design_rcp85)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='red', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.1)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], linestyle='--', color='red', alpha=0.5, linewidth=0.1)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gefüllte Fläche für die Standardabweichung von RCP8.5\n",
    "plt.fill_between(df_rcp_85['time'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] - df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 df_rcp_85['30_year_avg'] + df_rcp_85['30_year_std'], \n",
    "                 color='red', alpha=0.05, label='RCP8.5 - Std')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vertikale Linie zwischen 2023 und 2024 hinzufügen\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=pd.Timestamp('2024-01-01'), **design_trennlinie)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlim(df_reanalysis['time'].min(), df_rcp_45['time'].max())\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, df_reanalysis['cdd'].max() + 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Jahr', **design_xlabel)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Trockentage [d]', **design_ylabel)\n",
    "plt.title(f'Aufeinanderfolgende Trockentage für {aoi_name}', **design_title)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(**design_grid)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Untertitel\n",
    "plt.figtext(0.5, -0.05, untertitel , **design_figtext)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X-Achse: 10 Jahre-Intervall\n",
    "years = pd.date_range(start=df_reanalysis['time'].min(), end=df_rcp_85['time'].max(), freq='10YE').year\n",
    "plt.xticks(pd.to_datetime(years, format='%Y'), years, rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9bb1a194-118b-42de-8a07-875d25783874",
   "metadata": {
    "jp-MarkdownHeadingCollapsed": true
   },
   "source": [
    "#### 19. Dauer der meteorologischen Dürren\n",
    "Die \"Dauer der meteorologischen Dürre\" ist ein Index mit hoher Priorität, der die Gesamtzahl der Monate Monate mit anomal niedrigen Niederschlagsbedingungen (für mindestens zwei aufeinanderfolgende Monate) in einem bestimmten Zeitraum auf der Grundlage des standardisierten Niederschlagsindex (SPI). Verschiedene Implementierungen des SPI verwenden unterschiedliche Zeitaggregationen und Schwellenwerte für Niederschlagswerte. Der Index Der hier vorgestellte Index basiert auf dem aggregierten 3-Monats-Niederschlag (SPI-3), der im Allgemeinen als für landwirtschaftliche Anwendungen geeignet ist, und einem Schwellenwert von -1 für die Erkennung von von Trockenheitsereignissen. Weder SPI noch SPI-basierte Indizes sind derzeit in der C3S CDS verfügbar, aber die zugrundeliegenden Niederschlagsdaten sind ohne weiteres verfügbar. SPI-3 für vergangene und aktuelle Zeiträume ist aus dem C3S-Datensatz für Indizes auf der Grundlage von E-OBS-Daten leicht verfügbar. Dürrebedingungen auf der Grundlage des SPI werden auch von der EDO-Plattform der GFS überwacht. \n",
    "\n",
    "- Indikator: Dauer der meteorologischen Dürreperioden\n",
    "- Einheit: Monat\n",
    "- Beschreibung: Die Anzahl der Monate in einem Jahr mit anomal niedrigen Niederschlagsbedingungen auf der Grundlage des standardisierten 3-Monats-Niederschlagsindex (SPI-3) im Vergleich zu einem Referenzzeitraum, hier 1981-2010."
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from scipy.interpolate import UnivariateSpline\n",
    "\n",
    "#Duration of meteorological droughts [month]\n",
    "# The count of months in a year with anomalously low precipitation conditions based on the 3-month Standardised Precipitation Index (SPI-3) relative to a reference period, here 1981-2010.\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateipfade\n",
    "path_reanalysis = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_19_duration_of_meteorological_droughts_reanalysis_historical.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_45 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_19_duration_of_meteorological_droughts_projections_rcp_4_5.csv'\n",
    "path_rcp_85 = f'{aoi_directory}\\{aoi_name}_19_duration_of_meteorological_droughts_projections_rcp_8_5.csv'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Einlesen der Daten\n",
    "df_reanalysis = pd.read_csv(path_reanalysis)\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_45)\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = pd.read_csv(path_rcp_85)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertieren der Zeitspalte in Datetime-Objekte\n",
    "df_reanalysis['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_reanalysis['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_45['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_45['time'])\n",
    "df_rcp_85['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df_rcp_85['time'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Filtern der Daten basierend auf den Jahren\n",
    "df_reanalysis = df_reanalysis[(df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year >= 1940) & (df_reanalysis['time'].dt.year <= 2023)]\n",
    "df_rcp_45 = df_rcp_45[(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "df_rcp_85 = df_rcp_85[(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year >= 2024) & (df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year <= 2100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot erstellen\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=plot_settings['figsize'])\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({'font.family': plot_settings['font.family']})\n",
    "\n",
    "# Reanalyse-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_reanalysis['time'], df_reanalysis['dmd'], **design_reanalyse)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP4.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], df_rcp_45['dmd'], **design_rcp45)\n",
    "# # Trendlinie für RCP4.5 berechnen und plotten\n",
    "z = np.polyfit(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year, df_rcp_45['dmd'], 1)\n",
    "p = np.poly1d(z)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_45['time'], p(df_rcp_45['time'].dt.year), **design_rcp45_trend)\n",
    "\n",
    "# RCP8.5-Daten plotten\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], df_rcp_85['dmd'], **design_rcp85)\n",
    "# # Trendlinie für RCP8.5 berechnen und plotten\n",
    "z = np.polyfit(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year, df_rcp_85['dmd'], 1)\n",
    "p = np.poly1d(z)\n",
    "plt.plot(df_rcp_85['time'], p(df_rcp_85['time'].dt.year), **design_rcp85_trend)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vertikale Linie zwischen 2023 und 2024 hinzufügen\n",
    "plt.axvline(x=pd.Timestamp('2024-01-01'), **design_trennlinie)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlim(df_reanalysis['time'].min(), df_rcp_45['time'].max())\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, 12)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Jahr', **design_xlabel)\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Dürreperiode [Monat]', **design_ylabel)\n",
    "plt.title(f'Dauer von meteorologischen Dürren in {aoi_name}', **design_title)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(**design_grid)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Untertitel\n",
    "plt.figtext(0.5, -0.05, untertitel , **design_figtext)\n",
    "\n",
    "# X-Achse: 10 Jahre-Intervall\n",
    "years = pd.date_range(start=df_reanalysis['time'].min(), end=df_rcp_85['time'].max(), freq='10YE').year\n",
    "plt.xticks(pd.to_datetime(years, format='%Y'), years, rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n"

   "source": [
    "#### 22. Tage mit hoher Brandgefahr\n",
    "\"Tage mit hoher Brandgefahr\" ist ein Index von hoher Priorität, der die Häufigkeit gefährlicher Bedingungen auf der Grundlage von Wetterbedingungen bewertet, die sich auf die Brennstofffeuchtigkeit und das Brandverhalten auswirken. \n",
    "In der Brandgefahrenbewertung des Europäischen Waldbrandsystems (EFFIS) stehen FWI-Werte über 11,2, 21,3 und 38,0 für eine mäßige, hohe bzw. sehr hohe Brandgefahr. Verschiedene Implementierungen dieses Index verwenden unterschiedliche Schwellenwerte, die verschiedene Klassen der Brandgefahr definieren. Gefahr definieren. Der Index ist in der C3S unter Brandgefahrindikatoren für Europa, basierend auf EURO-CORDEX-Projektionen und aus den historischen Daten der Brandgefahr-Indizes auf der Grundlage der ERA5-Reanalyse. \n",
    "FWI-Projektionen für Europa wurden auch im Rahmen des GFS-Projekts PESETA III entwickelt. \n",
    "\n",
    "- Indikator: Tage mit hoher Brandgefahr\n",
    "- Einheit: Tag [d]\n",
    "- Beschreibung: Die Anzahl der Tage in einem Zeitraum mit einem Brandwetterindex (FWI) von mehr als 30 (Anzahl der Tage), basierend auf der Klassifizierung des Europäischen Waldbrandinformationssystems (EFFIS)."
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",

      "GeoTIFF für Jahr 2094 gespeichert: 'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Results\\05_tropical_nights_projections_rcp_8_5_2094.tif'\n",
      "GeoTIFF für Jahr 2095 gespeichert: 'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Results\\05_tropical_nights_projections_rcp_8_5_2095.tif'\n",
      "GeoTIFF für Jahr 2096 gespeichert: 'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Results\\05_tropical_nights_projections_rcp_8_5_2096.tif'\n",
      "GeoTIFF für Jahr 2097 gespeichert: 'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Results\\05_tropical_nights_projections_rcp_8_5_2097.tif'\n",
      "GeoTIFF für Jahr 2098 gespeichert: 'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Results\\05_tropical_nights_projections_rcp_8_5_2098.tif'\n",
      "GeoTIFF für Jahr 2099 gespeichert: 'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Results\\05_tropical_nights_projections_rcp_8_5_2099.tif'\n",
      "GeoTIFF für Jahr 2100 gespeichert: 'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Results\\05_tropical_nights_projections_rcp_8_5_2100.tif'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import rasterio\n",
    "from rasterio.transform import from_origin\n",
    "from rasterio.crs import CRS\n",
    "import netCDF4 as nc\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from netCDF4 import num2date\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the working folder and output folder (make sure these are defined)\n",
    "# working_folder = 'path/to/working_folder'\n",
    "# output_folder = 'path/to/output_folder'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Liste aller NetCDF-Dateien im Arbeitsordner\n",
    "netcdf_files = [f for f in os.listdir(working_folder) if f.endswith('.nc')]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Anzeige der verfügbaren Dateien und Auswahl durch den Benutzer\n",
    "print(\"Verfügbare NetCDF-Dateien:\")\n",
    "for i, file in enumerate(netcdf_files, start=1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}: {file}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "file_selection = input(\"Wähle die Nummern der zu verarbeitenden Dateien aus (mit Komma getrennt) oder 'alle' für alle Dateien: \")\n",
    "\n",
    "if file_selection.lower() == 'alle':\n",
    "    selected_files = netcdf_files\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    selected_indices = [int(i) - 1 for i in file_selection.split(',')]\n",
    "    selected_files = [netcdf_files[i] for i in selected_indices]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mapping von Indikator-Variablen\n",
    "indicator_variable_mapping = {\n",
    "    \"02_growing_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"03_heating_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"04_cooling_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"05_tropical_nights\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"06_hot_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"07_warmest_three_day_period\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"09_heat_waves_climatological\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"10_high_utci_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"high_utci_days\"},\n",
    "    \"11_frost_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"12_total_precipitation\": {\"reanalysis\": \"tp\", \"projections\": \"prAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"13_maximum_five_days_precipitation\": {\"reanalysis\": \"tp\", \"projections\": \"prAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"14_extreme_precipitation_total\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"15_frequency_of_extreme_precipitation\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"18_consecutive_dry_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"cdd\", \"projections\": \"cdd\"},\n",
    "    \"19_duration_of_meteorological_droughts\": {\"reanalysis\": \"dmd\", \"projections\": \"dmd\"},\n",
    "    \"20_magnitude_of_meteorological_droughts\": {\"reanalysis\": \"dmd\", \"projections\": \"dmd\"},\n",
    "    \"22_days_with_high_fire_danger\": {\"reanalysis\": \"fwi\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"24_extreme_wind_speed_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Deutschland Begrenzungen (in Grad)\n",
    "germany_bounds = {\n",
    "    'min_lon': 5.866,  # westliche Grenze\n",
    "    'max_lon': 15.042,  # östliche Grenze\n",
    "    'min_lat': 47.270,  # südliche Grenze\n",
    "    'max_lat': 55.058   # nördliche Grenze\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Extrahieren der Metadaten aus dem Dateinamen\n",
    "def extract_metadata(filename):\n",
    "    parts = filename.split('-')\n",
    "    indicator = parts[0]\n",
    "    experiment = parts[1]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if indicator == '06_hot_days':\n",
    "        deg = parts[3]\n",
    "        scenario = parts[4] if experiment != 'reanalysis' else 'historical'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        scenario = parts[3] if experiment == 'projections' else 'historical'\n",
    "        deg = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return indicator, experiment, scenario, deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertiere Längenwerte von 0-360 nach -180 bis 180, falls erforderlich\n",
    "def convert_longitudes(lons):\n",
    "    return np.where(lons > 180, lons - 360, lons)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zur Handhabung von 2D- oder 3D-Variablen\n",
    "def get_data_variable(ds, variable_name):\n",
    "    var = ds.variables[variable_name]\n",
    "    if len(var.shape) == 3:\n",
    "        return var[:, :, :]\n",
    "    elif len(var.shape) == 2:\n",
    "        return var[:, :]\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f\"Unerwartete Dimension der Variable {variable_name}: {var.shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    # Schleife über alle ausgewählten NetCDF-Dateien\n",
    "    for netcdf_file in selected_files:\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Datei-Pfad\n",
    "            input_netCDF = os.path.join(working_folder, netcdf_file)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Metadaten extrahieren\n",
    "            indicator, experiment, scenario, deg = extract_metadata(netcdf_file)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # NetCDF-Datei öffnen\n",
    "            ds = nc.Dataset(input_netCDF)\n",
    "            latitudes = ds.variables['lat'][:]\n",
    "            longitudes = ds.variables['lon'][:]\n",
    "            time_var = ds.variables['time']\n",
    "            time_units = ds.variables['time'].units\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Falls Längenwerte im Bereich 0 bis 360 sind, konvertiere sie\n",
    "            longitudes = convert_longitudes(longitudes)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Finde die Indizes der zu verwendenden Breiten und Längen\n",
    "            if latitudes[0] > latitudes[-1]:  # Wenn die lat-Achse absteigend ist, umdrehen\n",
    "                latitudes = latitudes[::-1]\n",
    "                tas_data = get_data_variable(ds, indicator_variable_mapping[indicator][experiment])[:, ::-1, :]\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                tas_data = get_data_variable(ds, indicator_variable_mapping[indicator][experiment])\n",
    "\n",
    "            lat_inds = np.where((latitudes >= germany_bounds['min_lat']) & (latitudes <= germany_bounds['max_lat']))[0]\n",
    "            lon_inds = np.where((longitudes >= germany_bounds['min_lon']) & (longitudes <= germany_bounds['max_lon']))[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Zuschneiden der Variablen auf die Indizes\n",
    "            tas_adjust_cropped = tas_data[:, lat_inds, :][:, :, lon_inds]\n",
    "            latitudes_cropped = latitudes[lat_inds]\n",
    "            longitudes_cropped = longitudes[lon_inds]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Berechne den Abstand zwischen den Längen- und Breitengraden\n",
    "            pixel_height = np.abs(latitudes_cropped[1] - latitudes_cropped[0])\n",
    "            pixel_width = np.abs(longitudes_cropped[1] - longitudes_cropped[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Transformationsparameter für die obere linke Ecke\n",
    "            transform = from_origin(\n",
    "                west=longitudes_cropped.min() - pixel_width / 2,\n",
    "                north=latitudes_cropped.max() + pixel_height / 2,\n",
    "                xsize=pixel_width,\n",
    "                ysize=pixel_height\n",
    "            )\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Definiere das CRS (WGS84)\n",
    "            crs = CRS.from_epsg(4326)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Erstelle die GeoTIFFs\n",
    "            for i, time_value in enumerate(time_var):\n",
    "                # Erstelle den Dateinamen\n",
    "                year = int(num2date(time_value, units=time_units).year)\n",
    "                if deg is not None:\n",
    "                    filename = f'{indicator}_{deg}_{experiment}_{scenario}_{year}.tif'\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    filename = f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{scenario}_{year}.tif'\n",
    "\n",
    "                # Umkehren der vertikalen Achse (Flip Up-Down)\n",
    "                tas_adjust_flipped = np.flipud(tas_adjust_cropped[i, :, :])\n",
    "\n",
    "                # Schreiben Sie die GeoTIFF-Datei\n",
    "                geotiff_path = os.path.join(output_folder, filename)\n",
    "                with rasterio.open(\n",
    "                    geotiff_path,\n",
    "                    'w',\n",
    "                    driver='GTiff',\n",
    "                    height=tas_adjust_flipped.shape[0],\n",
    "                    width=tas_adjust_flipped.shape[1],\n",
    "                    count=1,\n",
    "                    #dtype=tas_adjust_flipped.dtype,\n",
    "                    dtype='float32',\n",
    "                    crs=crs,\n",
    "                    transform=transform,\n",
    "                ) as dst:\n",
    "                    dst.write(tas_adjust_flipped, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "                print(f\"GeoTIFF für Jahr {year} gespeichert: '{geotiff_path}'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Datei schließen\n",
    "            ds.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"Fehler beim Verarbeiten der Datei {input_netCDF}: {e}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Allgemeiner Fehler: {e}\")\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import rasterio\n",
    "from rasterio.transform import from_origin\n",
    "from rasterio.crs import CRS\n",
    "import netCDF4 as nc\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from netCDF4 import num2date\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define the working folder and output folder (make sure these are defined)\n",
    "# working_folder = 'path/to/working_folder'\n",
    "# output_folder = 'path/to/output_folder'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Liste aller NetCDF-Dateien im Arbeitsordner\n",
    "netcdf_files = [f for f in os.listdir(working_folder) if f.endswith('.nc')]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Extrahieren der Metadaten aus dem Dateinamen\n",
    "def extract_metadata(filename):\n",
    "    parts = filename.split('-')\n",
    "    indicator = parts[0]\n",
    "    experiment = parts[1]\n",
    "    scenario = parts[3] if experiment == 'projections' else 'historical'\n",
    "    return indicator, experiment, scenario\n",
    "\n",
    "# Dateien nach Indikatoren gruppieren\n",
    "grouped_files = {}\n",
    "for file in netcdf_files:\n",
    "    indicator, experiment, scenario = extract_metadata(file)\n",
    "    if indicator not in grouped_files:\n",
    "        grouped_files[indicator] = []\n",
    "    grouped_files[indicator].append((experiment, scenario, file))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Anzeige der verfügbaren Indikatoren und Auswahl durch den Benutzer\n",
    "print(\"Verfügbare Indikatoren:\")\n",
    "indicators = list(grouped_files.keys())\n",
    "for i, indicator in enumerate(indicators, start=1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}: {indicator}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "indicator_selection = input(\"Wähle die Nummer des Indikators aus: \")\n",
    "selected_indicator = indicators[int(indicator_selection) - 1]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Anzeige der Dateien innerhalb des ausgewählten Indikators\n",
    "print(f\"\\nVerfügbare Dateien für '{selected_indicator}':\")\n",
    "files = grouped_files[selected_indicator]\n",
    "for i, (experiment, scenario, file) in enumerate(files, start=1):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i}: {experiment} - {scenario} - {file}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "file_selection = input(\"Wähle die Nummern der zu verarbeitenden Dateien aus (mit Komma getrennt) oder 'alle' für alle Dateien: \")\n",
    "\n",
    "if file_selection.lower() == 'alle':\n",
    "    selected_files = [file for _, _, file in files]\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    selected_indices = [int(i) - 1 for i in file_selection.split(',')]\n",
    "    selected_files = [files[i][2] for i in selected_indices]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Mapping von Indikator-Variablen\n",
    "indicator_variable_mapping = {\n",
    "    \"02_growing_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"03_heating_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"04_cooling_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"05_tropical_nights\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"06_hot_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"07_warmest_three_day_period\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"09_heat_waves_climatological\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"10_high_utci_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"high_utci_days\"},\n",
    "    \"11_frost_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"12_total_precipitation\": {\"reanalysis\": \"tp\", \"projections\": \"prAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"13_maximum_five_days_precipitation\": {\"reanalysis\": \"tp\", \"projections\": \"prAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"14_extreme_precipitation_total\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"15_frequency_of_extreme_precipitation\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"18_consecutive_dry_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"cdd\", \"projections\": \"cdd\"},\n",
    "    \"19_duration_of_meteorological_droughts\": {\"reanalysis\": \"dmd\", \"projections\": \"dmd\"},\n",
    "    \"20_magnitude_of_meteorological_droughts\": {\"reanalysis\": \"dmd\", \"projections\": \"dmd\"},\n",
    "    \"22_days_with_high_fire_danger\": {\"reanalysis\": \"fwi\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"24_extreme_wind_speed_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Deutschland Begrenzungen (in Grad)\n",
    "germany_bounds = {\n",
    "    'min_lon': 5.866,  # westliche Grenze\n",
    "    'max_lon': 15.042,  # östliche Grenze\n",
    "    'min_lat': 47.270,  # südliche Grenze\n",
    "    'max_lat': 55.058   # nördliche Grenze\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Extrahieren der Metadaten aus dem Dateinamen\n",
    "def extract_metadata(filename):\n",
    "    parts = filename.split('-')\n",
    "    indicator = parts[0]\n",
    "    experiment = parts[1]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if indicator == '06_hot_days':\n",
    "        deg = parts[3]\n",
    "        scenario = parts[4] if experiment != 'reanalysis' else 'historical'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        scenario = parts[3] if experiment == 'projections' else 'historical'\n",
    "        deg = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return indicator, experiment, scenario, deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konvertiere Längenwerte von 0-360 nach -180 bis 180, falls erforderlich\n",
    "def convert_longitudes(lons):\n",
    "    return np.where(lons > 180, lons - 360, lons)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zur Handhabung von 2D- oder 3D-Variablen\n",
    "def get_data_variable(ds, variable_name):\n",
    "    var = ds.variables[variable_name]\n",
    "    if len(var.shape) == 3:\n",
    "        return var[:, :, :]\n",
    "    elif len(var.shape) == 2:\n",
    "        return var[:, :]\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f\"Unerwartete Dimension der Variable {variable_name}: {var.shape}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    # Schleife über alle ausgewählten NetCDF-Dateien\n",
    "    for netcdf_file in selected_files:\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            # Datei-Pfad\n",
    "            input_netCDF = os.path.join(working_folder, netcdf_file)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Metadaten extrahieren\n",
    "            indicator, experiment, scenario, deg = extract_metadata(netcdf_file)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # NetCDF-Datei öffnen\n",
    "            ds = nc.Dataset(input_netCDF)\n",
    "            latitudes = ds.variables['lat'][:]\n",
    "            longitudes = ds.variables['lon'][:]\n",
    "            time_var = ds.variables['time']\n",
    "            time_units = ds.variables['time'].units\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Falls Längenwerte im Bereich 0 bis 360 sind, konvertiere sie\n",
    "            longitudes = convert_longitudes(longitudes)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Finde die Indizes der zu verwendenden Breiten und Längen\n",
    "            if latitudes[0] > latitudes[-1]:  # Wenn die lat-Achse absteigend ist, umdrehen\n",
    "                latitudes = latitudes[::-1]\n",
    "                tas_data = get_data_variable(ds, indicator_variable_mapping[indicator][experiment])[:, ::-1, :]\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                tas_data = get_data_variable(ds, indicator_variable_mapping[indicator][experiment])\n",
    "\n",
    "            lat_inds = np.where((latitudes >= germany_bounds['min_lat']) & (latitudes <= germany_bounds['max_lat']))[0]\n",
    "            lon_inds = np.where((longitudes >= germany_bounds['min_lon']) & (longitudes <= germany_bounds['max_lon']))[0]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Zuschneiden der Variablen auf die Indizes\n",
    "            tas_adjust_cropped = tas_data[:, lat_inds, :][:, :, lon_inds]\n",
    "            latitudes_cropped = latitudes[lat_inds]\n",
    "            longitudes_cropped = longitudes[lon_inds]\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Berechne den Abstand zwischen den Längen- und Breitengraden\n",
    "            pixel_height = np.abs(latitudes_cropped[1] - latitudes_cropped[0])\n",
    "            pixel_width = np.abs(longitudes_cropped[1] - longitudes_cropped[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Transformationsparameter für die obere linke Ecke\n",
    "            transform = from_origin(\n",
    "                west=longitudes_cropped.min() - pixel_width / 2,\n",
    "                north=latitudes_cropped.max() + pixel_height / 2,\n",
    "                xsize=pixel_width,\n",
    "                ysize=pixel_height\n",
    "            )\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Definiere das CRS (WGS84)\n",
    "            crs = CRS.from_epsg(4326)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Erstelle die GeoTIFFs\n",
    "            for i, time_value in enumerate(time_var):\n",
    "                # Erstelle den Dateinamen\n",
    "                year = int(num2date(time_value, units=time_units).year)\n",
    "                if deg is not None:\n",
    "                    filename = f'{indicator}_{deg}_{experiment}_{scenario}_{year}.tif'\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    filename = f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{scenario}_{year}.tif'\n",
    "\n",
    "                # Umkehren der vertikalen Achse (Flip Up-Down)\n",
    "                tas_adjust_flipped = np.flipud(tas_adjust_cropped[i, :, :])\n",
    "\n",
    "                # Schreiben Sie die GeoTIFF-Datei\n",
    "                geotiff_path = os.path.join(output_folder, filename)\n",
    "                with rasterio.open(\n",
    "                    geotiff_path,\n",
    "                    'w',\n",
    "                    driver='GTiff',\n",
    "                    height=tas_adjust_flipped.shape[0],\n",
    "                    width=tas_adjust_flipped.shape[1],\n",
    "                    count=1,\n",
    "                    #dtype=tas_adjust_flipped.dtype,\n",
    "                    dtype='float32',\n",
    "                    crs=crs,\n",
    "                    transform=transform,\n",
    "                ) as dst:\n",
    "                    dst.write(tas_adjust_flipped, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "                print(f\"GeoTIFF für Jahr {year} gespeichert: '{geotiff_path}'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Datei schließen\n",
    "            ds.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"Fehler beim Verarbeiten der Datei {input_netCDF}: {e}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Allgemeiner Fehler: {e}\")\n"
   ]

   "source": [
    "# Downscaling auf AOI Bodensee mit 1000 x 1000 m Auflösung\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import rasterio\n",
    "from rasterio.transform import from_origin\n",
    "from rasterio.crs import CRS\n",
    "from rasterio.enums import Resampling\n",
    "from rasterio.warp import reproject, Resampling\n",
    "from netCDF4 import Dataset, num2date\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import shutil\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definiere den Zielbereich (AOI) durch Koordinaten für den Bodensee\n",
    "# min_lon = 7.5 # 8.9 Bodensee\n",
    "# max_lon = 10.5 # 10.3 Bodensee\n",
    "# min_lat = 47.5 # 47.3 Bodensee\n",
    "# max_lat = 49.8 # 48.0 Bodensee\n",
    "\n",
    "min_lon = 12.2731 # Leipzig\n",
    "max_lon = 12.4731 # Leipzig\n",
    "min_lat = 51.2397 # Leipzig\n",
    "max_lat = 51.4397 # Leipzig\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definiere die Auflösung des Zielrasters\n",
    "target_res = 500  # in Metern\n",
    "\n",
    "# NetCDF-Datei öffnen\n",
    "ds = Dataset(input_netCDF)\n",
    "lat = ds.variables['lat'][:]\n",
    "lon = ds.variables['lon'][:]\n",
    "time_var = ds.variables['time']\n",
    "time_units = ds.variables['time'].units  # Zeit-Einheiten ablesen\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bestimme die Pixelgröße und den Ursprung\n",
    "pixel_size_lat = (lat.max() - lat.min()) / (len(lat) - 1)\n",
    "pixel_size_lon = (lon.max() - lon.min()) / (len(lon) - 1)\n",
    "transform = from_origin(lon.min(), lat.max(), pixel_size_lon, pixel_size_lat)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definiere das CRS (WGS84)\n",
    "crs = CRS.from_epsg(4326)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Berechne die Dimensionen des Zielrasters\n",
    "target_width = int((max_lon - min_lon) * 111320 / target_res)  # 1 Grad entspricht ca. 111320 Meter\n",
    "target_height = int((max_lat - min_lat) * 110574 / target_res)  # 1 Grad entspricht ca. 110574 Meter\n",
    "\n",
    "# Berechne die Transformationsmatrix für das Zielraster\n",
    "target_transform = from_origin(min_lon, max_lat, target_res / 111320, target_res / 110574)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Unterordner für unprozessierte GeoTIFFs erstellen\n",
    "unprocessed_dir = os.path.join(output_folder, 'unprocessed')\n",
    "os.makedirs(unprocessed_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Unterordner für heruntergerechnete GeoTIFFs erstellen\n",
    "downscaled_dir = os.path.join(output_folder, 'downscaled')\n",
    "os.makedirs(downscaled_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    # Schleife über alle Zeitdaten\n",
    "    for t in range(len(time_var)):\n",
    "        # Daten für den aktuellen Zeitstempel lesen\n",
    "        data = ds.variables[variable][t, :, :]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Jahr aus der Zeitvariable extrahieren\n",
    "        year = int(num2date(time_var[t], time_units).year)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Speichern als unprozessierter GeoTIFF\n",
    "        geotiff_path = os.path.join(unprocessed_dir, f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{year}.tiff')\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(\n",
    "            geotiff_path,\n",
    "            'w',\n",
    "            driver='GTiff',\n",
    "            height=data.shape[0],\n",
    "            width=data.shape[1],\n",
    "            count=1,\n",
    "            dtype=data.dtype,\n",
    "            crs=crs,\n",
    "            transform=transform\n",
    "        ) as dst:\n",
    "            dst.write(data, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Bild um 180° drehen und von links nach rechts spiegeln\n",
    "        rotated_data = np.rot90(data, k=2)\n",
    "        flipped_data = np.fliplr(rotated_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Speichern des bearbeiteten GeoTIFFs\n",
    "        processed_path = os.path.join(output_folder, f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{year}_processed.tiff')\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(\n",
    "            processed_path,\n",
    "            'w',\n",
    "            driver='GTiff',\n",
    "            height=flipped_data.shape[0],\n",
    "            width=flipped_data.shape[1],\n",
    "            count=1,\n",
    "            dtype=flipped_data.dtype,\n",
    "            crs=crs,\n",
    "            transform=transform\n",
    "        ) as dst:\n",
    "            dst.write(flipped_data, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(f\"GeoTIFF für Jahr {year} gespeichert: '{geotiff_path}' und bearbeitet als '{processed_path}'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Downscaling der GeoTIFF-Datei\n",
    "        downscaled_path = os.path.join(downscaled_dir, f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{year}_downscaled.tiff')\n",
    "\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(processed_path) as src:\n",
    "            # Erstelle die neue Datei\n",
    "            with rasterio.open(\n",
    "                downscaled_path, 'w', driver='GTiff', height=target_height, width=target_width,\n",
    "                count=1, dtype=src.dtypes[0], crs=crs, transform=target_transform\n",
    "            ) as dst:\n",
    "                # Reprojectiere die Daten mit linearer Interpolation\n",
    "                reproject(\n",
    "                    source=rasterio.band(src, 1),\n",
    "                    destination=rasterio.band(dst, 1),\n",
    "                    src_transform=transform,\n",
    "                    src_crs=crs,\n",
    "                    dst_transform=target_transform,\n",
    "                    dst_crs=crs,\n",
    "                    resampling=Resampling.bilinear\n",
    "                )\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(f\"Heruntergerechneter GeoTIFF für Jahr {year} gespeichert als: '{downscaled_path}'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Datei schließen\n",
    "    ds.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Löschen des unprozessierten Ordners und seiner Inhalte\n",
    "    shutil.rmtree(unprocessed_dir)\n",
    "    print(f\"Der Ordner '{unprocessed_dir}' und seine Inhalte wurden gelöscht.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Fehler beim Öffnen der Datei {input_netCDF}: {e}\")\n"
   ]
  },

   "id": "831c6c84-6cc9-4c18-9e22-f84e57b2ad98",

    "## E. Zeitreihen als GIF darstellen (UNVOLLSTÄNDIG) [netCDF -> Gif]\n",
    "Bei origin = projections wird der Zeitraum 2024 - 2100 geplottet, für reanalysis 1940 - 2023. Um den Zeitraum 1940 - 2100 als GIF zu erhalten, den Schritt 3.1 für origin und projection ausführen. Aktuell fixe Legende / colorbar von vmin = 0 bis vmax = 20"

    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import netCDF4 as nc\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import os\n",
    "from datetime import datetime\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap\n",
    "\n",
    "def create_map(lat, lon, data, title, output_path, cmap, vmin, vmax, plot_type='contourf'):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Create and save a plot with Basemap.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Parameters:\n",
    "    - lat: Latitude values\n",
    "    - lon: Longitude values\n",
    "    - data: Data to plot\n",
    "    - title: Plot title\n",
    "    - output_path: Path to save the plot\n",
    "    - cmap: Colormap\n",
    "    - vmin: Minimum value of the colormap\n",
    "    - vmax: Maximum value of the colormap\n",
    "    - plot_type: Type of plot ('contourf' or 'imshow')\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        # Create Basemap for Germany\n",
    "        m = Basemap(projection='merc', llcrnrlat=47.3, urcrnrlat=55.0,\n",
    "                    llcrnrlon=5.9, urcrnrlon=15.0, resolution='l')\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Add rivers, coastlines, and country borders\n",
    "        m.drawrivers(color='b', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "        m.drawcoastlines()\n",
    "        m.drawcountries(linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Coordinates for major German cities\n",
    "        # cities = {\n",
    "        #     'Berlin': (52.52, 13.405),\n",
    "        #     'Hamburg': (53.551, 9.993),\n",
    "        #     'München': (48.135, 11.582),\n",
    "        #     'Stuttgart': (48.775, 9.182),\n",
    "        #     'Düsseldorf': (51.225, 6.776),\n",
    "        #     'Wiesbaden': (50.082, 8.241),\n",
    "        #     'Schwerin': (53.635, 11.412),\n",
    "        #     'Hannover': (52.374, 9.738),\n",
    "        #     'Saarbrücken': (49.234, 6.997),\n",
    "        #     'Dresden': (51.050, 13.737),\n",
    "        #     'Magdeburg': (52.120, 11.629),\n",
    "        #     'Kiel': (54.323, 10.139),\n",
    "        #     'Erfurt': (50.978, 11.029),\n",
    "        #     'Bremen': (53.075, 8.807),\n",
    "        # }\n",
    "\n",
    "        cities = {\n",
    "        'Berlin': (52.520, 13.405, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Hamburg': (53.551, 9.993, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'München': (48.135, 11.582, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Stuttgart': (48.775, 9.182, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Düsseldorf': (51.225, 6.776, -1000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Wiesbaden': (50.082, 8.241, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Schwerin': (53.635, 11.412, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Hannover': (52.374, 9.738, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Saarbrücken': (49.234, 6.997, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Dresden': (51.050, 13.737, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Magdeburg': (52.120, 11.629, -50000, -40000, 9),\n",
    "        'Kiel': (54.323, 10.139, -30000, -35000, 9),\n",
    "        'Erfurt': (50.978, 11.029, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Bremen': (53.075, 8.807, -20000, 20000, 9),\n",
    "        'Potsdam': (52.390, 13.064, -50000, -30000, 9),\n",
    "        'Mainz': (50.000, 8.271, -55000, -30000, 9),\n",
    "        }\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Plot cities on the map\n",
    "        for city, (lat_city, lon_city) in cities.items():\n",
    "            x, y = m(lon_city, lat_city)\n",
    "            m.plot(x, y, 'ro', markersize=8)\n",
    "            plt.text(x + 15000, y - 10000, city, fontsize=9, ha='left', color='black')\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Plot the data\n",
    "        lon, lat = np.meshgrid(lon, lat)\n",
    "        x, y = m(lon, lat)\n",
    "        data_masked = np.ma.masked_invalid(data)\n",
    "        cmap.set_bad(color=(0, 0, 0, 0))  # Set color for invalid values to transparent\n",
    "\n",
    "        if plot_type == 'contourf':\n",
    "            m.contourf(x, y, data_masked, cmap=cmap, vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax)\n",
    "        elif plot_type == 'imshow':\n",
    "            m.imshow(data_masked, extent=[lon.min(), lon.max(), lat.min(), lat.max()],\n",
    "                     origin='lower', aspect='auto', cmap=cmap, vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Add a title above the plot\n",
    "        plt.suptitle(title, fontsize=18,)\n",
    "        # Adjust spacing to reduce gap between plot and title\n",
    "        plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.94)  # Adjust the top parameter to bring the title closer\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Adjust the position of the colorbar\n",
    "        cbar_ax = plt.gcf().add_axes([0.80, 0.11, 0.04, 0.82])  # Moved closer by reducing the first value\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Create the colorbar\n",
    "        cb = mpl.colorbar.ColorbarBase(cbar_ax, cmap=cmap, norm=mpl.colors.Normalize(vmin=vmin, vmax=vmax), orientation='vertical')\n",
    "        cb.set_label(f'{indicator}', size=12)  # Add label to the colorbar\n",
    "        \n",
    "        plt.savefig(output_path, bbox_inches='tight', pad_inches=0.1)\n",
    "        plt.close()\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Fehler beim Erstellen des Plots für {title}: {e}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "def main():\n",
    "    file_path = input_netCDF\n",
    "    #output_folder = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\HWD\\PNG'\n",
    "    #os.makedirs(output_folder, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    dataset2 = nc.Dataset(file_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "    time_var = dataset2.variables['time']\n",
    "    time_units = time_var.units\n",
    "    time_data = nc.num2date(time_var[:], units=time_units)\n",
    "\n",
    "    variable_name = variable\n",
    "    global_min = np.inf\n",
    "    global_max = -np.inf\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Determine the time range based on the origin\n",
    "    if origin == 'reanalysis':\n",
    "        start_year = 1940\n",
    "        end_year = 2023\n",
    "    elif origin == 'projections':\n",
    "        start_year = 2024\n",
    "        end_year = 2100\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(\"Unknown origin: Please specify 'reanalysis' or 'projections'.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Calculate global min and max values for the colormap scale\n",
    "    for year in range(start_year, end_year + 1):\n",
    "        desired_time = datetime(year, 1, 1, 0)\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            time_index = np.where(time_data == desired_time)[0][0]\n",
    "        except IndexError:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        data = dataset2.variables[variable_name][time_index, :, :]\n",
    "        data_min = np.min(data)\n",
    "        data_max = np.max(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "        if data_min < global_min:\n",
    "            global_min = data_min\n",
    "        if data_max > global_max:\n",
    "            global_max = data_max\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f'Global min: {global_min}, Global max: {global_max}')\n",
    "\n",
    "    cmap = plt.cm.coolwarm\n",
    "    vmin, vmax = 0, 20\n",
    "\n",
    "    for year in range(start_year, end_year + 1):\n",
    "        desired_time = datetime(year, 1, 1, 0)\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            time_index = np.where(time_data == desired_time)[0][0]\n",
    "        except IndexError:\n",
    "            print(f\"Zeitpunkt {desired_time} nicht gefunden, überspringe Jahr {year}\")\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(year)\n",
    "\n",
    "        data = dataset2.variables[variable_name][time_index, :, :]\n",
    "        lat = dataset2.variables['lat'][:]\n",
    "        lon = dataset2.variables['lon'][:]\n",
    "\n",
    "        if np.isnan(data).any() or np.isinf(data).any():\n",
    "            print(f\"Ungültige Werte in den Daten für {desired_time}, überspringe Jahr {year}\")\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        data_min = np.min(data)\n",
    "        data_max = np.max(data)\n",
    "        if data_min == data_max:\n",
    "            print(f\"Konstante Werte in den Daten für {desired_time}, überspringe Jahr {year}\")\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "\n",
    "        create_map(lat, lon, data, f'Jahr {desired_time.year} - {origin}', \n",
    "                   os.path.join(output_folder, f'{indicator}_{year}.png'), \n",
    "                   cmap, vmin, vmax, plot_type='contourf')\n",
    "\n",
    "        if not os.path.exists(os.path.join(output_folder, f'{indicator}_{year}.png')):\n",
    "            create_map(lat, lon, data, f'Jahr {desired_time.year} - RCP8.5', \n",
    "                       os.path.join(output_folder, f'{indicator}_{year}.png'), \n",
    "                       cmap, vmin, vmax, plot_type='imshow')\n",
    "\n",
    "if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n",
    "    main()\n"
   ]

    "import os\n",

    "import imageio\n",

    "# Verzeichnis mit den PNG-Bildern\n",
    "#input_folder = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\HWD\\PNG'\n",

    "\n",
    "# Name der Ausgabedatei\n",
    "output_gif = f'{indicator}_animation.gif'\n",
    "output_path = os.path.join(output_folder, output_gif)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Liste der PNG-Bilder sortieren\n",
    "images = []\n",

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
