   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from geopy.distance import geodesic\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "from shapely.geometry import Point, box\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from mpl_toolkits.basemap import Basemap\n",
    "\n",
    "# Parameter festlegen\n",
    "csv_directory = output_folder\n",
    "radius_km = 40\n",
    "grid_size_km = 10  # Größe des Rasters in Kilometern\n",
    "\n",
    "# Schritt 1: Erste CSV-Datei im Verzeichnis auswählen\n",
    "csv_files = [f for f in os.listdir(csv_directory) if f.endswith('.csv')]\n",
    "if len(csv_files) == 0:\n",
    "    raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Keine CSV-Dateien im Verzeichnis {csv_directory} gefunden.\")\n",
    "first_csv_file = os.path.join(csv_directory, csv_files[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Schritt 2: CSV-Datei einlesen und nach dem Jahr 2000 filtern\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(first_csv_file)\n",
    "df['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df['time'])\n",
    "df_2000 = df[df['time'].dt.year == 2000].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Schritt 3: Koordinaten innerhalb des Radius von 40 km um die AOI finden\n",
    "def is_within_radius(lat, lon, center_lat, center_lon, radius_km):\n",
    "    return geodesic((lat, lon), (center_lat, center_lon)).km <= radius_km\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2000['within_radius'] = df_2000.apply(lambda row: is_within_radius(row['latitude'], row['longitude'], aoi_latitude, aoi_longitude, radius_km), axis=1)\n",
    "df_within_radius = df_2000[df_2000['within_radius']]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Geometrie-Spalte hinzufügen\n",
    "df_within_radius['geometry'] = df_within_radius.apply(lambda row: Point(row['longitude'], row['latitude']), axis=1)\n",
    "gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(df_within_radius, geometry='geometry')\n",
    "\n",
    "# AOI als Punkt definieren\n",
    "aoi_point = Point(aoi_longitude, aoi_latitude)\n",
    "aoi_gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame([{'geometry': aoi_point, 'name': aoi_name}], crs=\"EPSG:4326\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Raster-Gitter erstellen\n",
    "def create_grid(center_lat, center_lon, grid_size_km, radius_km):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Erzeuge ein Raster um den Mittelpunkt (center_lat, center_lon).\"\"\"\n",
    "    delta = grid_size_km / 111  # Umrechnung von Kilometern in Breitengrad\n",
    "    longitudes = np.arange(center_lon - radius_km / 111, center_lon + radius_km / 111, delta)\n",
    "    latitudes = np.arange(center_lat - radius_km / 111, center_lat + radius_km / 111, delta)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Rasterlinien als Polygone erstellen\n",
    "    grid_polygons = []\n",
    "    for lat in latitudes:\n",
    "        for lon in longitudes:\n",
    "            grid_polygons.append(box(lon, lat, lon + delta, lat + delta))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return gpd.GeoDataFrame({'geometry': grid_polygons}, crs=\"EPSG:4326\")\n",
    "\n",
    "grid_gdf = create_grid(aoi_latitude, aoi_longitude, grid_size_km, radius_km)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Umwandlung der Koordinaten für Basemap\n",
    "def latlon_to_xy(lat, lon, map_obj):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Konvertiere Latitude/Longitude in x/y für Basemap.\"\"\"\n",
    "    x, y = map_obj(lon, lat)\n",
    "    return x, y\n",
    "\n",
    "# Basemap erstellen\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 12))\n",
    "m = Basemap(projection='merc', \n",
    "            llcrnrlat=aoi_latitude - 1, urcrnrlat=aoi_latitude + 1, \n",
    "            llcrnrlon=aoi_longitude - 1, urcrnrlon=aoi_longitude + 1, \n",
    "            resolution='i', ax=ax)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Blue Marble-Stil als Hintergrund verwenden\n",
    "m.bluemarble()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Raster-Gitter auf der Basemap darstellen\n",
    "for _, row in grid_gdf.iterrows():\n",
    "    coords = [latlon_to_xy(lat, lon, m) for lon, lat in list(row['geometry'].exterior.coords)]\n",
    "    m.plot(*zip(*coords), marker=None, color='gray', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Punkte und AOI auf der Basemap darstellen\n",
    "for _, row in gdf.iterrows():\n",
    "    x, y = latlon_to_xy(row['latitude'], row['longitude'], m)\n",
    "    m.plot(x, y, 'bo', markersize=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "x_aoi, y_aoi = latlon_to_xy(aoi_latitude, aoi_longitude, m)\n",
    "m.plot(x_aoi, y_aoi, 'rx', markersize=10)\n",
    "\n",

    "\n",
    "# Karte anzeigen\n",
    "plt.show()\n"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "609f095c-8cd2-459d-86c7-d78bcd2eaee3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import re\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion, um alle .nc-Dateien im Arbeitsverzeichnis abzurufen\n",
    "def get_nc_files(working_folder):\n",
    "    return [f for f in os.listdir(working_folder) if f.endswith('.nc')]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Liste der verfügbaren Dateien im Arbeitsverzeichnis\n",
    "files = get_nc_files(working_folder)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Datensatz-Variable Mapping\n",
    "dataset_variable_mapping = {\n",
    "    \"02_growing_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"03_heating_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"04_cooling_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"05_tropical_nights\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"06_hot_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"07_warmest_three_day_period\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"09_heat_waves_climatological\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"10_high_utci_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"high_utci_days\"},\n",
    "    \"11_frost_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zur Auswahl der Datei\n",
    "def select_dataset():\n",
    "    # Erstelle eine Liste der einzigartigen Datensatznamen (Nummer und Bezeichnung)\n",
    "    dataset_names = sorted(list(set(f.split('-')[0] for f in files)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "    print(\"Bitte wählen Sie einen Datensatz aus:\")\n",
    "    for idx, name in enumerate(dataset_names):\n",
    "        print(f\"{idx+1}: {name}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benutzereingabe für Datensatz\n",
    "    dataset_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer des Datensatzes ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "    selected_dataset = dataset_names[dataset_idx]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return selected_dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "def select_origin(dataset):\n",
    "    if dataset == \"10_high_utci_days\":\n",
    "        return \"reanalysis\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Filtere die Dateien für den ausgewählten Datensatz\n",
    "    relevant_files = [f for f in files if f.startswith(dataset)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Bestimme die möglichen Origins (reanalysis, projections)\n",
    "    origins = sorted(list(set(f.split('-')[1] for f in relevant_files)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "    print(\"Bitte wählen Sie die Origin aus:\")\n",
    "    for idx, origin in enumerate(origins):\n",
    "        print(f\"{idx+1}: {origin}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benutzereingabe für Origin\n",
    "    origin_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer der Origin ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "    selected_origin = origins[origin_idx]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return selected_origin\n",
    "\n",
    "def select_degree(dataset, origin):\n",
    "    if dataset == \"06_hot_days\":\n",
    "        # Filtere die Dateien für den ausgewählten Datensatz und Origin\n",
    "        relevant_files = [f for f in files if f.startswith(dataset) and origin in f]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Bestimme die möglichen Gradwerte (30deg, 35deg, 40deg)\n",
    "        degrees = sorted(list(set(re.search(r'\\d+deg', f).group(0) for f in relevant_files if re.search(r'\\d+deg', f))))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "        print(\"Bitte wählen Sie den Gradwert aus:\")\n",
    "        for idx, degree in enumerate(degrees):\n",
    "            print(f\"{idx+1}: {degree}\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Benutzereingabe für Gradwert\n",
    "        degree_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer des Gradwerts ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "        selected_degree = degrees[degree_idx]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return selected_degree\n",
    "    return None\n",
    "\n",
    "def select_rcp(dataset, origin):\n",
    "    # Filtere die Dateien für den ausgewählten Datensatz und Origin\n",
    "    relevant_files = [f for f in files if f.startswith(dataset) and origin in f]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if origin == 'projections':\n",
    "        # Bestimme die möglichen RCP-Scenarios (rcp_4_5, rcp_8_5)\n",
    "        rcps = sorted(list(set(re.search(r'rcp_\\d_\\d', f).group(0) for f in relevant_files if re.search(r'rcp_\\d_\\d', f))))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "        print(\"Bitte wählen Sie das RCP-Szenario aus:\")\n",
    "        for idx, rcp in enumerate(rcps):\n",
    "            print(f\"{idx+1}: {rcp}\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Benutzereingabe für RCP\n",
    "        rcp_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer des RCP-Szenarios ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "        selected_rcp = rcps[rcp_idx]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return selected_rcp\n",
    "    return None\n",
    "\n",
    "# Auswahlprozess\n",
    "selected_dataset = select_dataset()\n",
    "selected_origin = select_origin(selected_dataset)\n",
    "selected_degree = select_degree(selected_dataset, selected_origin) if selected_dataset == \"06_hot_days\" else None\n",
    "selected_rcp = select_rcp(selected_dataset, selected_origin) if selected_origin == 'projections' else None\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bestimme die entsprechende Datei\n",
    "if selected_degree and selected_rcp:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_dataset in f and selected_origin in f and selected_degree in f and selected_rcp in f][0]\n",
    "elif selected_degree:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_dataset in f and selected_origin in f and selected_degree in f][0]\n",
    "elif selected_rcp:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_dataset in f and selected_origin in f and selected_rcp in f][0]\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_dataset in f and selected_origin in f][0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Speichere die entsprechende Variable basierend auf der Auswahl\n",
    "variable = dataset_variable_mapping[selected_dataset][selected_origin]\n",
    "experiment = selected_rcp if selected_origin == 'projections' else 'historic'\n",
    "origin = selected_origin\n",
    "\n",
    "# Speichern des ausgewählten Datensatzes und Gradwerts falls vorhanden\n",
    "if selected_dataset == \"06_hot_days\" and selected_degree:\n",
    "    dataset = f\"{selected_dataset}_{selected_degree}\"\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    dataset = selected_dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "# Falls die Ordner noch nicht existieren, diese erstellen\n",
    "input_netCDF = os.path.join(working_folder, relevant_file)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ausgabe der Ergebnisse\n",
    "print(f\"Ausgewählte Datei: {relevant_file}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Entsprechende Variable: {variable}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Szenario: {experiment}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Datensatz: {dataset}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Herkunft: {origin}\")"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7fdfaebd-39c1-41f2-8293-37999c2253b2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from netCDF4 import Dataset, num2date\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "\n",
    "nc_file = input_netCDF\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Umwandeln von netCDF in CSV\n",
    "def netcdf_to_dataframe(nc_file):\n",
    "    # Öffne die netCDF Datei\n",
    "    dataset = input_netCDF\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Extrahiere die spezifische Variable und die Zeit\n",
    "    if variable in dataset.variables and 'time' in dataset.variables:\n",
    "        temperature = dataset.variables[variable][:]\n",
    "        time = dataset.variables['time'][:]\n",
    "        lat = dataset.variables['lat'][:]\n",
    "        lon = dataset.variables['lon'][:]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Konvertiere die Zeit in ein lesbares Format\n",
    "        time_units = dataset.variables['time'].units\n",
    "        time_calendar = dataset.variables['time'].calendar if hasattr(dataset.variables['time'], 'calendar') else 'standard'\n",
    "        time = num2date(time, units=time_units, calendar=time_calendar)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Finde die Indizes, die in den definierten Ausschnitt fallen\n",
    "        lat_indices = (lat >= lat_min) & (lat <= lat_max)\n",
    "        lon_indices = (lon >= lon_min) & (lon <= lon_max)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Filtere Ausschnitt\n",
    "        filtered_lat = lat[lat_indices]\n",
    "        filtered_lon = lon[lon_indices]\n",
    "        filtered_temperature = temperature[:, lat_indices, :][:, :, lon_indices]\n",
    "\n",
    "        #variable =  f'{nc_file}'\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Erstelle eine Liste von Einträgen für das DataFrame\n",
    "        rows = []\n",
    "        for t in range(filtered_temperature.shape[0]):\n",
    "            for i in range(filtered_temperature.shape[1]):\n",
    "                for j in range(filtered_temperature.shape[2]):\n",
    "                    if not filtered_temperature.mask[t, i, j]:\n",
    "                        rows.append({\n",
    "                            'time': time[t],\n",
    "                            'latitude': filtered_lat[i],\n",
    "                            'longitude': filtered_lon[j],\n",
    "                            variable: filtered_temperature[t, i, j]\n",
    "                        })\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Erstelle ein DataFrame aus den Einträgen\n",
    "        df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\n",
    "        df['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df['time'].map(str))\n",
    "        df['latitude'] = pd.to_numeric(df['latitude'])\n",
    "        df['longitude'] = pd.to_numeric(df['longitude'])\n",
    "        df[variable] = pd.to_numeric(df[variable])\n",
    "        return df.set_index(['time', 'latitude', 'longitude'])\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        raise ValueError(f'Variables not found in {nc_file}')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Schließe das Dataset\n",
    "    dataset.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Erstelle das Ausgabe-Verzeichnis, falls es nicht existiert\n",
    "os.makedirs(\"data/hacs-csv\", exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Durchlaufe Szenarien/Statistiken\n",
    "dataframes = [ netcdf_to_dataframe(nc_file) for nc_file in tqdm(nc_files) ]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Kombiniere alle Daten in eine Tabelle\n",
    "df = pd.concat(dataframes, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Schreibe CSV\n",
    "df.to_csv('sis-heat-and-cold-spells.csv.zip', sep=',', encoding='utf8', compression='zip')\n",
    "\n",
    "df"
   ]
  },

   "id": "3dbdb853-1659-4c1e-9341-d6aa7d323691",

    "# convert from wide to long format\n",
    "kn_long = (\n",
    "    kn\n",
    "    .reset_index()\n",
    "    .melt(id_vars=['time', 'longitude', 'latitude'])\n",
    "    .assign(scenario = lambda x: x.variable.map(lambda s: s.split('-')[0]))\n",
    "    .assign(variable = lambda x: x.variable.map(lambda s: s.split('-')[1]))\n",
    "    .pivot(index=['time', 'longitude', 'latitude', 'scenario'], columns=['variable'], values=['value'])\n",
    "    .reset_index()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "kn_long.columns = ['time', 'longitude', 'latitude', 'scenario', 'mean', 'stdev']\n",
    "kn_long"

   "cell_type": "code",

   "id": "179c047a-a7e2-4499-ac9b-ebe9501fd476",

    "for s in kn_long['scenario'].drop_duplicates():\n",
    "    d = kn_long.query(f'scenario == \"{s}\"')\n",
    "    x = d['time']\n",
    "    y = d['mean']\n",
    "    err = d['stdev']\n",
    "    plt.plot(x, y, label=f'{s}-mean')\n",
    "    plt.fill_between(x, y-err, y+err, alpha=0.3, label=f'{s}-stdev')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title('Erwartete Hitzewellentage pro Jahr in Konstanz')\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Zeit\")\n",
    "plt.legend(loc=\"upper left\", title='Szenario')\n",
    "plt.show()"

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1a426a28-bf4b-4176-a6a2-e01c5dfa183d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "########## Output-Datei mehr als 7GB groß... \n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import xarray as xr\n",
    "import rasterio\n",
    "from rasterio.transform import from_origin\n",
    "from rasterio.crs import CRS\n",
    "from rasterio.enums import Resampling\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import shutil\n",
    "from netCDF4 import Dataset, num2date\n",
    "from rasterio.warp import calculate_default_transform, reproject\n",
    "\n",
    "# Konfiguriere die Eingabepfade\n",
    "#input_netCDF = 'path/to/your/input/netCDF.nc'\n",
    "output_folder = r\"C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Ergebnis\\Interpolated\"\n",
    "aoi_raster_path = r\"C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Input\\AOI_Raster2.tif\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# AOI-Raster laden und seine Eigenschaften extrahieren\n",
    "with rasterio.open(aoi_raster_path) as aoi_raster:\n",
    "    aoi_crs = aoi_raster.crs\n",
    "    aoi_transform = aoi_raster.transform\n",
    "    aoi_width = aoi_raster.width\n",
    "    aoi_height = aoi_raster.height\n",
    "    aoi_res = aoi_raster.res\n",
    "\n",
    "# NetCDF-Datei öffnen\n",
    "ds = Dataset(input_netCDF)\n",
    "lat = ds.variables['lat'][:]\n",
    "lon = ds.variables['lon'][:]\n",
    "time_var = ds.variables['time']\n",
    "time_units = ds.variables['time'].units  # Zeit-Einheiten ablesen\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bestimme die Pixelgröße und den Ursprung\n",
    "pixel_size_lat = (lat.max() - lat.min()) / (len(lat) - 1)\n",
    "pixel_size_lon = (lon.max() - lon.min()) / (len(lon) - 1)\n",
    "transform = from_origin(lon.min(), lat.max(), pixel_size_lon, pixel_size_lat)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definiere das CRS (WGS84)\n",
    "crs = CRS.from_epsg(4326)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Unterordner für unprozessierte GeoTIFFs erstellen\n",
    "unprocessed_dir = os.path.join(output_folder, 'unprocessed')\n",
    "os.makedirs(unprocessed_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Unterordner für heruntergerechnete GeoTIFFs erstellen\n",
    "downscaled_dir = os.path.join(output_folder, 'downscaled')\n",
    "os.makedirs(downscaled_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    # Schleife über alle Zeitdaten\n",
    "    for t in range(len(time_var)):\n",
    "        variable_name = variable\n",
    "        # Daten für den aktuellen Zeitstempel lesen\n",
    "        data = ds.variables[variable_name][t, :, :]\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Jahr aus der Zeitvariable extrahieren\n",
    "        year = int(num2date(time_var[t], time_units).year)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Speichern als unprozessierter GeoTIFF\n",
    "        geotiff_path = os.path.join(unprocessed_dir, f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{year}.tiff')\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(\n",
    "            geotiff_path,\n",
    "            'w',\n",
    "            driver='GTiff',\n",
    "            height=data.shape[0],\n",
    "            width=data.shape[1],\n",
    "            count=1,\n",
    "            dtype=data.dtype,\n",
    "            crs=crs,\n",
    "            transform=transform\n",
    "        ) as dst:\n",
    "            dst.write(data, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Bild um 180° drehen und von links nach rechts spiegeln\n",
    "        rotated_data = np.rot90(data, k=2)\n",
    "        flipped_data = np.fliplr(rotated_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Speichern des bearbeiteten GeoTIFFs\n",
    "        processed_path = os.path.join(output_folder, f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{year}_processed.tiff')\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(\n",
    "            processed_path,\n",
    "            'w',\n",
    "            driver='GTiff',\n",
    "            height=flipped_data.shape[0],\n",
    "            width=flipped_data.shape[1],\n",
    "            count=1,\n",
    "            dtype=flipped_data.dtype,\n",
    "            crs=crs,\n",
    "            transform=transform\n",
    "        ) as dst:\n",
    "            dst.write(flipped_data, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(f\"GeoTIFF für Jahr {year} gespeichert: '{geotiff_path}' und bearbeitet als '{processed_path}'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Downscaling der GeoTIFF-Datei\n",
    "        downscaled_path = os.path.join(downscaled_dir, f'{indicator}_{experiment}_{year}_downscaled.tiff')\n",
    "        \n",
    "        with rasterio.open(processed_path) as src:\n",
    "            # Berechne die neue Transformationsmatrix\n",
    "            new_transform, width, height = calculate_default_transform(\n",
    "                src.crs, aoi_crs, src.width, src.height, *src.bounds, resolution=aoi_res\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Erstelle die neue Datei\n",
    "            with rasterio.open(\n",
    "                downscaled_path, 'w', driver='GTiff', height=height, width=width,\n",
    "                count=1, dtype=src.dtypes[0], crs=aoi_crs, transform=new_transform\n",
    "            ) as dst:\n",
    "                # Reprojectiere die Daten\n",
    "                reproject(\n",
    "                    source=rasterio.band(src, 1),\n",
    "                    destination=rasterio.band(dst, 1),\n",
    "                    src_crs=src.crs,\n",
    "                    dst_crs=aoi_crs,\n",
    "                    resampling=Resampling.bilinear\n",
    "                )\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(f\"Heruntergerechneter GeoTIFF für Jahr {year} gespeichert als: '{downscaled_path}'\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Datei schließen\n",
    "    ds.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Löschen des unprozessierten Ordners und seiner Inhalte\n",
    "    shutil.rmtree(unprocessed_dir)\n",
    "    print(f\"Der Ordner '{unprocessed_dir}' und seine Inhalte wurden gelöscht.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Fehler beim Öffnen der Datei {input_netCDF}: {e}\")\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "382bc04d-a87a-4675-8955-0b0d69ccf892",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#### nur null werte...\n",
    "\n",
    "import rasterio\n",
    "from rasterio.transform import from_origin\n",
    "from rasterio.warp import reproject, Resampling\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "def read_geotiff(file_path):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(file_path) as src:\n",
    "            data = src.read(1)\n",
    "            transform = src.transform\n",
    "            crs = src.crs\n",
    "        print(f\"Successfully read {file_path}\")\n",
    "        return data, transform, crs\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Error reading {file_path}: {e}\")\n",
    "        return None, None, None\n",
    "\n",
    "def create_aoi_raster(aoi_bounds, resolution=200):\n",
    "    x_min, y_min, x_max, y_max = aoi_bounds\n",
    "    width = int((x_max - x_min) / resolution)\n",
    "    height = int((y_max - y_min) / resolution)\n",
    "    transform = from_origin(x_min, y_max, resolution, resolution)\n",
    "    return width, height, transform\n",
    "\n",
    "def resample_to_aoi(geotiff_data, geotiff_transform, geotiff_crs, aoi_transform, aoi_width, aoi_height):\n",
    "    aoi_data = np.empty((aoi_height, aoi_width), dtype=geotiff_data.dtype)\n",
    "    reproject(\n",
    "        source=geotiff_data,\n",
    "        destination=aoi_data,\n",
    "        src_transform=geotiff_transform,\n",
    "        src_crs=geotiff_crs,\n",
    "        dst_transform=aoi_transform,\n",
    "        dst_crs=geotiff_crs,\n",
    "        resampling=Resampling.bilinear  # oder Resampling.nearest\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return aoi_data\n",
    "\n",
    "def save_geotiff(output_path, data, transform, crs):\n",
    "    try:\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(\n",
    "            output_path, 'w', driver='GTiff', height=data.shape[0], width=data.shape[1], count=1,\n",
    "            dtype=str(data.dtype), crs=crs, transform=transform) as dst:\n",
    "            dst.write(data, 1)\n",
    "        print(f\"Successfully saved resampled data to {output_path}\")\n",
    "    except Exception as e:\n",
    "        print(f\"Error saving {output_path}: {e}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "aoi_shapefile = r\"C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Input\\Konstanz_Mask.shp\"\n",
    "try:\n",
    "    aoi_gdf = gpd.read_file(aoi_shapefile)\n",
    "    aoi_bounds = aoi_gdf.total_bounds  # xmin, ymin, xmax, ymax\n",
    "    print(f\"AOI Bounds: {aoi_bounds}\")\n",
    "except Exception as e:\n",
    "    print(f\"Error reading AOI shapefile: {e}\")\n",
    "    aoi_bounds = None\n",
    "\n",
    "if aoi_bounds is not None:\n",
    "    geotiff_directory = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Ergebnis\\GeoTIFF'\n",
    "    output_directory = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Ergebnis\\Interpolated'\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not os.path.exists(output_directory):\n",
    "        os.makedirs(output_directory)\n",
    "        print(f\"Created output directory: {output_directory}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not os.path.exists(geotiff_directory):\n",
    "        print(f\"GeoTIFF directory does not exist: {geotiff_directory}\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        geotiff_files = [f for f in os.listdir(geotiff_directory) if f.endswith('.tiff')]\n",
    "        print(f\"Found {len(geotiff_files)} files in GeoTIFF directory\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        aoi_width, aoi_height, aoi_transform = create_aoi_raster(aoi_bounds, resolution=200)\n",
    "        print(f\"AOI Raster: width={aoi_width}, height={aoi_height}, transform={aoi_transform}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        for filename in geotiff_files:\n",
    "            geotiff_path = os.path.join(geotiff_directory, filename)\n",
    "            print(f\"Processing {geotiff_path}\")\n",
    "            \n",
    "            geotiff_data, geotiff_transform, geotiff_crs = read_geotiff(geotiff_path)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if geotiff_data is None:\n",
    "                print(f\"Skipping {geotiff_path} due to read error.\")\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "            \n",
    "            print(f\"GeoTIFF Data Shape: {geotiff_data.shape}, Transform: {geotiff_transform}, CRS: {geotiff_crs}\")\n",
    "            print(f\"GeoTIFF Data Sample Values: {geotiff_data[0:5, 0:5]}\")  # Output first 5x5 values for debug\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if np.isnan(geotiff_data).all():\n",
    "                print(f\"All values in {geotiff_path} are NaN. Skipping this file.\")\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "            \n",
    "            try:\n",
    "                resampled_data = resample_to_aoi(geotiff_data, geotiff_transform, geotiff_crs, aoi_transform, aoi_width, aoi_height)\n",
    "                print(f\"Resampled Data Shape: {resampled_data.shape}\")\n",
    "                print(f\"Resampled Data Sample Values: {resampled_data[0:5, 0:5]}\")  # Output first 5x5 values for debug\n",
    "                \n",
    "                output_path = os.path.join(output_directory, f'resampled_{filename}')\n",
    "                save_geotiff(output_path, resampled_data, aoi_transform, geotiff_crs)\n",
    "            except Exception as e:\n",
    "                print(f\"Error processing {geotiff_path}: {e}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        print(\"Finished processing all GeoTIFF files.\")\n",
    "print(\"Script completed.\")\n"
   ]
  },

    "dummy_crs = 'EPSG:32632'  # Beispiel-CRS, anpassen nach Bedarf\n",

    "save_geotiff(r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Ergebnis\\Interpolated\\dummy_test.tif', dummy_data, dummy_transform, dummy_crs)\n"

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ac52ca23-19e2-4b40-8992-88f7bc368752",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import rasterio\n",
    "from rasterio.enums import Resampling\n",
    "\n",
    "def resample_raster(input_raster_path, output_raster_path, target_width, target_height):\n",
    "    with rasterio.open(input_raster_path) as src:\n",
    "        # Calculate new transform and dimensions\n",
    "        new_transform = src.transform * src.transform.scale(\n",
    "            (src.width / target_width),\n",
    "            (src.height / target_height)\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        new_width = target_width\n",
    "        new_height = target_height\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Read and resample data\n",
    "        data = src.read(\n",
    "            out_shape=(src.count, new_height, new_width),\n",
    "            resampling=Resampling.bilinear\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Update metadata\n",
    "        metadata = src.meta.copy()\n",
    "        metadata.update({\n",
    "            'height': new_height,\n",
    "            'width': new_width,\n",
    "            'transform': new_transform\n",
    "        })\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Write resampled data\n",
    "        with rasterio.open(output_raster_path, 'w', **metadata) as dest:\n",
    "            dest.write(data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Path to the directory containing the GeoTIFFs\n",
    "input_directory = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Ergebnis\\GeoTIFF'\n",
    "output_directory = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\Heat\\Ergebnis\\Interpolated'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Path to the input and output files\n",
    "years = range(1950, 1956)  # Example range, adjust as needed\n",
    "for year in years:\n",
    "    input_raster_path = f'{input_directory}\\\\05_tropical_nights_rcp_8_5_{year}_processed.tiff'\n",
    "    output_raster_path = f'{output_directory}\\\\resampled_05_tropical_nights_rcp_8_5_{year}_processed.tiff'\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Resample the raster to the AOI resolution (49, 60) or as required\n",
    "    resample_raster(input_raster_path, output_raster_path, 49, 60)\n"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definieren Sie das Verzeichnis, in dem sich die CSV-Dateien befinden\n",
    "csv_directory = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\CSV'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Toleranzbereich für die Koordinaten\n",
    "tolerance = 0.13\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Extrahieren der Metadaten aus dem Dateinamen\n",
    "def extract_metadata(filename):\n",
    "    parts = filename.split('-')\n",
    "    indicator = parts[0]\n",
    "    experiment = parts[1]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if indicator == '06_hot_days':\n",
    "        deg = parts[3]\n",
    "        scenario = parts[4] if experiment != 'reanalysis' else 'historical'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        scenario = parts[3] if experiment == 'projections' else 'historical'\n",
    "        deg = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return indicator, experiment, scenario, deg\n",
    "\n",
    "# # AOI-Koordinaten (setzen Sie diese entsprechend Ihrer Region)\n",
    "# aoi_latitude = 51.3397  # Beispielwert für Leipzig\n",
    "# aoi_longitude = 12.3731  # Beispielwert für Leipzig\n",
    "\n",
    "# Iterieren Sie durch alle CSV-Dateien im Verzeichnis\n",
    "for filename in os.listdir(csv_directory):\n",
    "    if filename.endswith('.csv'):\n",
    "        file_path = os.path.join(csv_directory, filename)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Laden der CSV-Datei\n",
    "        df = pd.read_csv(file_path)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Filtern der Werte für das AOI\n",
    "        aoi_df = df[(df['latitude'].between(aoi_latitude - tolerance, aoi_latitude + tolerance)) & \n",
    "                        (df['longitude'].between(aoi_longitude - tolerance, aoi_longitude + tolerance))]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Extrahieren der Metadaten aus dem Dateinamen\n",
    "        indicator, experiment, scenario, deg = extract_metadata(filename)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Benennung der neuen CSV-Datei\n",
    "        if indicator == '06_hot_days':\n",
    "            new_filename = f'{aoi_name}_{indicator}_{deg}_{experiment}_{scenario}.csv'\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            new_filename = f'{aoi_name}_{indicator}_{experiment}_{scenario}.csv'\n",
    "        \n",
    "        csv_output = os.path.join(aoi_directory, new_filename)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Speichern der gefilterten Werte in einer neuen CSV-Datei\n",
    "        aoi_df.to_csv(csv_output, index=False)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        print(f\"Datei gespeichert: {csv_output}\")\n"
   ]

   "source": [
    "## CSV-Export anhand der AOI, zunächst Auswahl der Koordinaten\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definieren Sie das Verzeichnis, in dem sich die CSV-Dateien befinden\n",
    "csv_directory = r'C:\\Users\\timte\\Documents\\Python\\Climate Indicators\\CSV'\n",
    "\n",
    "# Toleranzbereich für die Koordinaten\n",
    "tolerance = 0.13\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zum Extrahieren der Metadaten aus dem Dateinamen\n",
    "def extract_metadata(filename):\n",
    "    parts = filename.split('-')\n",
    "    indicator = parts[0]\n",
    "    experiment = parts[1]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if indicator == '06_hot_days':\n",
    "        deg = parts[3]\n",
    "        scenario = parts[4] if experiment != 'reanalysis' else 'historical'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        scenario = parts[3] if experiment == 'projections' else 'historical'\n",
    "        deg = None\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return indicator, experiment, scenario, deg\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Variable zum Speichern der ausgewählten Koordinate\n",
    "selected_coordinate = None\n",
    "\n",
    "# Iterieren Sie durch alle CSV-Dateien im Verzeichnis\n",
    "for filename in os.listdir(csv_directory):\n",
    "    if filename.endswith('.csv'):\n",
    "        file_path = os.path.join(csv_directory, filename)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Laden der CSV-Datei\n",
    "        df = pd.read_csv(file_path)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Filtern der Werte für das AOI\n",
    "        aoi_df = df[(df['latitude'].between(aoi_latitude - tolerance, aoi_latitude + tolerance)) & \n",
    "                        (df['longitude'].between(aoi_longitude - tolerance, aoi_longitude + tolerance))]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        if not aoi_df.empty:\n",
    "            # Entfernen von Duplikaten basierend auf Latitude und Longitude\n",
    "            unique_coordinates = aoi_df[['latitude', 'longitude']].drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            if selected_coordinate is None:\n",
    "                if len(unique_coordinates) > 1:\n",
    "                    # Mehrere eindeutige Koordinaten im Toleranzbereich gefunden\n",
    "                    print(\"Mehrere eindeutige Koordinaten gefunden:\")\n",
    "                    for i, (lat, lon) in enumerate(unique_coordinates.values):\n",
    "                        print(f\"Option {i+1}: Latitude = {lat}, Longitude = {lon}\")\n",
    "                    \n",
    "                    # Benutzerauswahl\n",
    "                    selected_option = int(input(\"Wählen Sie eine Option aus (geben Sie die Nummer ein): \")) - 1\n",
    "                    selected_coordinate = unique_coordinates.iloc[selected_option]\n",
    "                else:\n",
    "                    print(f\"Eine eindeutige Koordinate im Toleranzbereich gefunden: Latitude = {unique_coordinates.iloc[0]['latitude']}, Longitude = {unique_coordinates.iloc[0]['longitude']}\")\n",
    "                    selected_coordinate = unique_coordinates.iloc[0]\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Filtern der Daten auf die ausgewählte Koordinate\n",
    "            aoi_df = aoi_df[(aoi_df['latitude'] == selected_coordinate['latitude']) & \n",
    "                            (aoi_df['longitude'] == selected_coordinate['longitude'])]\n",
    "        \n",
    "            # Extrahieren der Metadaten aus dem Dateinamen\n",
    "            indicator, experiment, scenario, deg = extract_metadata(filename)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Benennung der neuen CSV-Datei\n",
    "            if indicator == '06_hot_days':\n",
    "                new_filename = f'{aoi_name}_{indicator}_{deg}_{experiment}_{scenario}.csv'\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                new_filename = f'{aoi_name}_{indicator}_{experiment}_{scenario}.csv'\n",
    "            \n",
    "            csv_output = os.path.join(aoi_directory, new_filename)\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Speichern der gefilterten Werte in einer neuen CSV-Datei\n",
    "            aoi_df.to_csv(csv_output, index=False)\n",
    "            print(f\"Datei gespeichert: {csv_output}\")\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            print(f\"Keine Koordinaten im Toleranzbereich für {filename} gefunden.\")\n"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b133671e-bf8f-4aa6-bbf9-85029156adcb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "##Auswahl der Datensätze\n",
    "\n",
    "import re\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion, um alle .nc-Dateien im Arbeitsverzeichnis abzurufen\n",
    "def get_nc_files(working_folder):\n",
    "    return [f for f in os.listdir(working_folder) if f.endswith('.nc')]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Liste der verfügbaren Dateien im Arbeitsverzeichnis\n",
    "files = get_nc_files(working_folder)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Datensatz-Variable Mapping\n",
    "indicator_variable_mapping = {\n",
    "    \"02_growing_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"03_heating_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"04_cooling_degree_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"05_tropical_nights\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"06_hot_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "    \"07_warmest_three_day_period\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust\"},\n",
    "    \"09_heat_waves_climatological\": {\"reanalysis\": \"data\", \"projections\": \"data\"},\n",
    "    \"10_high_utci_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"high_utci_days\"},\n",
    "    \"11_frost_days\": {\"reanalysis\": \"t2m\", \"projections\": \"tasAdjust_NON_CDM\"},\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Funktion zur Auswahl der Datei\n",
    "def select_indicator():\n",
    "    # Erstelle eine Liste der einzigartigen Datensatznamen (Nummer und Bezeichnung)\n",
    "    indicator_names = sorted(list(set(f.split('-')[0] for f in files)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "    print(\"Bitte wählen Sie einen Datensatz aus:\")\n",
    "    for idx, name in enumerate(indicator_names):\n",
    "        print(f\"{idx+1}: {name}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benutzereingabe für Datensatz\n",
    "    indicator_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer des Datensatzes ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "    selected_indicator = indicator_names[indicator_idx]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return selected_indicator\n",
    "\n",
    "def select_origin(indicator):\n",
    "    if indicator == \"10_high_utci_days\":\n",
    "        return \"reanalysis\"\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Filtere die Dateien für den ausgewählten Datensatz\n",
    "    relevant_files = [f for f in files if f.startswith(indicator)]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Bestimme die möglichen Origins (reanalysis, projections)\n",
    "    origins = sorted(list(set(f.split('-')[1] for f in relevant_files)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "    print(\"Bitte wählen Sie die Origin aus:\")\n",
    "    for idx, origin in enumerate(origins):\n",
    "        print(f\"{idx+1}: {origin}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Benutzereingabe für Origin\n",
    "    origin_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer der Origin ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "    selected_origin = origins[origin_idx]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return selected_origin\n",
    "\n",
    "def select_degree(indicator, origin):\n",
    "    if indicator == \"06_hot_days\":\n",
    "        # Filtere die Dateien für den ausgewählten Datensatz und Origin\n",
    "        relevant_files = [f for f in files if f.startswith(indicator) and origin in f]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Bestimme die möglichen Gradwerte (30deg, 35deg, 40deg)\n",
    "        degrees = sorted(list(set(re.search(r'\\d+deg', f).group(0) for f in relevant_files if re.search(r'\\d+deg', f))))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "        print(\"Bitte wählen Sie den Gradwert aus:\")\n",
    "        for idx, degree in enumerate(degrees):\n",
    "            print(f\"{idx+1}: {degree}\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Benutzereingabe für Gradwert\n",
    "        degree_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer des Gradwerts ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "        selected_degree = degrees[degree_idx]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return selected_degree\n",
    "    return None\n",
    "\n",
    "def select_rcp(indicator, origin):\n",
    "    # Filtere die Dateien für den ausgewählten Datensatz und Origin\n",
    "    relevant_files = [f for f in files if f.startswith(indicator) and origin in f]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if origin == 'projections':\n",
    "        # Bestimme die möglichen RCP-Scenarios (rcp_4_5, rcp_8_5)\n",
    "        rcps = sorted(list(set(re.search(r'rcp_\\d_\\d', f).group(0) for f in relevant_files if re.search(r'rcp_\\d_\\d', f))))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Drucke die Auswahlmöglichkeiten\n",
    "        print(\"Bitte wählen Sie das RCP-Szenario aus:\")\n",
    "        for idx, rcp in enumerate(rcps):\n",
    "            print(f\"{idx+1}: {rcp}\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Benutzereingabe für RCP\n",
    "        rcp_idx = int(input(\"Geben Sie die Nummer des RCP-Szenarios ein: \")) - 1\n",
    "        selected_rcp = rcps[rcp_idx]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        return selected_rcp\n",
    "    return None\n",
    "\n",
    "# Auswahlprozess\n",
    "selected_indicator = select_indicator()\n",
    "selected_origin = select_origin(selected_indicator)\n",
    "selected_degree = select_degree(selected_indicator, selected_origin) if selected_indicator == \"06_hot_days\" else None\n",
    "selected_rcp = select_rcp(selected_indicator, selected_origin) if selected_origin == 'projections' else None\n",
    "\n",
    "# Bestimme die entsprechende Datei\n",
    "if selected_degree and selected_rcp:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_indicator in f and selected_origin in f and selected_degree in f and selected_rcp in f][0]\n",
    "elif selected_degree:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_indicator in f and selected_origin in f and selected_degree in f][0]\n",
    "elif selected_rcp:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_indicator in f and selected_origin in f and selected_rcp in f][0]\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    relevant_file = [f for f in files if selected_indicator in f and selected_origin in f][0]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Speichere die entsprechende Variable basierend auf der Auswahl\n",
    "variable = indicator_variable_mapping[selected_indicator][selected_origin]\n",
    "experiment = selected_rcp if selected_origin == 'projections' else 'historic'\n",
    "origin = selected_origin\n",
    "\n",
    "# Speichern des ausgewählten Datensatzes und Gradwerts falls vorhanden\n",
    "if selected_indicator == \"06_hot_days\" and selected_degree:\n",
    "    indicator = f\"{selected_indicator}_{selected_degree}\"\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    indicator = selected_indicator\n",
    "\n",
    "# Falls die Ordner noch nicht existieren, diese erstellen\n",
    "input_netCDF = os.path.join(working_folder, relevant_file)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ausgabe der Ergebnisse\n",
    "print(f\"Ausgewählte Datei: {relevant_file}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Entsprechende Variable: {variable}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Szenario: {experiment}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Datensatz: {indicator}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Herkunft: {origin}\")"
   ]
  },

      "text/plain": [
       "<folium.folium.Map at 0x1db3e64c450>"

     "execution_count": 17,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from geopy.distance import geodesic\n",
    "import folium\n",
    "from folium import plugins\n",
    "\n",
    "# Parameter festlegen\n",
    "csv_directory = output_folder\n",
    "radius_km = 40\n",
    "\n",
    "# Schritt 1: Erste CSV-Datei im Verzeichnis auswählen\n",
    "csv_files = [f for f in os.listdir(csv_directory) if f.endswith('.csv')]\n",
    "if len(csv_files) == 0:\n",
    "    raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Keine CSV-Dateien im Verzeichnis {csv_directory} gefunden.\")\n",
    "first_csv_file = os.path.join(csv_directory, csv_files[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Schritt 2: CSV-Datei einlesen und nach dem Jahr 2000 filtern\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(first_csv_file)\n",
    "df['time'] = pd.to_datetime(df['time'])\n",
    "df_2000 = df[df['time'].dt.year == 2000].copy()  # Verwende .copy(), um die Kopie explizit zu machen\n",
    "\n",
    "# Definiere die AOI Koordinaten und den Namen\n",
    "# aoi_latitude = 48.8588443  # Beispiel: Paris\n",
    "# aoi_longitude = 2.2943506  # Beispiel: Paris\n",
    "# aoi_name = \"AOI\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Schritt 3: Koordinaten innerhalb des Radius von 40 km um die AOI finden\n",
    "def is_within_radius(lat, lon, center_lat, center_lon, radius_km):\n",
    "    return geodesic((lat, lon), (center_lat, center_lon)).km <= radius_km\n",
    "\n",
    "df_2000['within_radius'] = df_2000.apply(\n",
    "    lambda row: is_within_radius(row['latitude'], row['longitude'], aoi_latitude, aoi_longitude, radius_km), \n",
    "    axis=1\n",
    ")\n",
    "df_within_radius = df_2000[df_2000['within_radius']]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Folium Karte erstellen\n",
    "m = folium.Map(location=[aoi_latitude, aoi_longitude], zoom_start=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "# AOI einzeichnen\n",
    "folium.Marker(\n",
    "    [aoi_latitude, aoi_longitude], \n",
    "    popup=f'AOI ({aoi_name})', \n",
    "    icon=folium.Icon(color='red')\n",
    ").add_to(m)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Koordinaten in der Nähe der AOI einzeichnen\n",
    "for _, row in df_within_radius.iterrows():\n",
    "    coords = f\"Lat: {row['latitude']}, Lon: {row['longitude']}\"\n",
    "    folium.Circle(\n",
    "        [row['latitude'], row['longitude']],\n",
    "        radius=500,\n",
    "        color='blue',\n",
    "        fill=True,\n",
    "        fill_color='blue',\n",
    "        popup=coords  # Beschriftung auf die Koordinaten setzen\n",
    "    ).add_to(m)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gitternetzlinien einzeichnen\n",
    "def draw_grid_lines(df):\n",
    "    grid_latitudes = df['grid_latitude'].unique()\n",
    "    grid_longitudes = df['grid_longitude'].unique()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Sortiere die Linien für konsistente Reihenfolge\n",
    "    grid_latitudes.sort()\n",
    "    grid_longitudes.sort()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Linien für horizontale Gitternetzlinien zeichnen\n",
    "    for lat in grid_latitudes:\n",
    "        # Linien entlang des Längengrads\n",
    "        folium.PolyLine(\n",
    "            locations=[(lat, min(grid_longitudes)), (lat, max(grid_longitudes))],\n",
    "            color='orange',\n",
    "            weight=2.5,\n",
    "            opacity=0.8\n",
    "        ).add_to(m)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Linien für vertikale Gitternetzlinien zeichnen\n",
    "    for lon in grid_longitudes:\n",
    "        # Linien entlang des Breitengrads\n",
    "        folium.PolyLine(\n",
    "            locations=[(min(grid_latitudes), lon), (max(grid_latitudes), lon)],\n",
    "            color='orange',\n",
    "            weight=2.5,\n",
    "            opacity=0.8\n",
    "        ).add_to(m)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Gitternetzpunkte aus der CSV-Datei einzeichnen\n",
    "if 'grid_latitude' in df.columns and 'grid_longitude' in df.columns:\n",
    "    draw_grid_lines(df)\n",
    "    for _, row in df.iterrows():\n",
    "        grid_lat = row['grid_latitude']\n",
    "        grid_lon = row['grid_longitude']\n",
    "        folium.Marker(\n",
    "            location=[grid_lat, grid_lon],\n",
    "            icon=folium.Icon(color='green', icon='info-sign'),\n",
    "            popup=f\"Grid Lat: {grid_lat}, Lon: {grid_lon}\"\n",
    "        ).add_to(m)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Karte speichern und anzeigen\n",
    "m.save('map.html')\n",
    "m\n"
   ]
  }
